WEBVTT

00:02.753 --> 00:04.175
PREVIOUSLY
ON "GREY'S ANATOMY"...

00:04.175 --> 00:05.716
Cristina: I COULD PRINT
A SCAFFOLDING AND -- AND MAKE

00:05.716 --> 00:06.927
A BIOLOGICAL CONDUIT
FOR A BABY'S HEART.

00:06.927 --> 00:08.429
THEY'RE NOT EVEN
DOING THAT YET.

00:08.429 --> 00:09.930
Man:
DR. YANG HIT A HOME RUN.

00:09.930 --> 00:12.303
THANKS TO HER,
BABY NATHAN IS THRIVING.

00:12.303 --> 00:14.345
Shane: AN E-MAIL FROM
THE HARPER AVERY FOUNDATION.

00:14.345 --> 00:16.477
WHAT?
YOU'RE IN CONSIDERATION
FOR THIS YEAR'S AWARD.

00:16.477 --> 00:18.269
WE...
WE ARE MARRIED.

00:18.269 --> 00:20.691
April: WE DID SOMETHING
THAT WASN'T RESPONSIBLE,

00:20.691 --> 00:22.523
BUT WE DID IT
BECAUSE WE LOVE EACH OTHER,

00:22.523 --> 00:24.195
AND WE WANT TO SPEND
EVERY DAY TOGETHER.

00:24.195 --> 00:25.696
Meredith: EMMA MARLING
AND OWEN ARE THROUGH.

00:25.696 --> 00:27.198
I DON'T THINK
IT WAS HER IDEA.

00:27.198 --> 00:28.569
HOPKINS WANTS ME!

00:28.569 --> 00:30.071
DID THEY THROW IN
A LOAN-REPAYMENT PACKAGE

00:30.071 --> 00:31.282
OR MOVING EXPENSES?

00:31.282 --> 00:32.953
WE DON'T HAVE
THE DOUGH, OKAY?

00:32.953 --> 00:34.995
I'M POSTPONING HOPKINS
TILL ROBBINS IS BETTER.

00:34.995 --> 00:36.827
IT'S BEAUTIFUL!

00:36.827 --> 00:38.329
AND IT'S GONNA BE OURS!

00:38.329 --> 00:41.252
I'D LIKE TO APPOINT YOU DIRECTOR
OF THE RESIDENCY PROGRAM.

00:41.252 --> 00:43.254
YOU'D BE IN CHARGE
OF ALL THE DECISIONS

00:43.254 --> 00:45.966
REGARDING THE EDUCATIONAL ARM
OF THIS HOSPITAL.

00:45.966 --> 00:48.089
MEREDITH, WHEN THE PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES

00:48.089 --> 00:49.800
CALLS YOU ON THE PHONE,
YOU CAN'T SAY NO TO THE GUY.

00:49.800 --> 00:51.262
YOU WENT BACK
ON YOUR PROMISE.

00:51.262 --> 00:52.933
YOU SAY THAT YOU WORK
SO HARD TO CHANGE,

00:52.933 --> 00:55.136
TO BECOME THIS NEW PERSON,
BUT THEN YOU DO THIS?

00:55.136 --> 00:56.637
SHE ATTACKED ME.
JO'S A LUNATIC.

00:56.637 --> 00:57.848
DAMN IT!
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

01:06.527 --> 01:08.859
Meredith: THE AVERAGE PERSON
TOUCHES THEIR FACE

01:08.859 --> 01:11.452
ABOUT 18 TIMES
EVERY WAKING HOUR.

01:11.452 --> 01:12.993
[ SNEEZES ]

01:12.993 --> 01:14.995
THAT LEAVES YOU SUSCEPTIBLE

01:14.995 --> 01:17.658
TO INFECTION
ABOUT 100 TIMES A DAY.

01:17.658 --> 01:20.621
WELL...
BLESS YOU, SWEETIE.

01:20.621 --> 01:24.004
INFECTION HAS A NASTY HABIT

01:24.004 --> 01:27.208
OF TAKING ADVANTAGE
OF OUR EVERYDAY BEHAVIORS.

01:27.208 --> 01:29.009
OKAY, I'M GONNA CALL
DR. LEBACKES

01:29.009 --> 01:30.171
AND MOVE UP
OUR ANOPLASTY

01:30.171 --> 01:32.092
BECAUSE I'M GONNA
BE SICK THIS AFTERNOON.

01:32.092 --> 01:33.174
WHAT ARE YOU, PSYCHIC?

01:33.174 --> 01:35.216
NO, I FELT IT --
YOU KNOW, THE SICK.

01:35.216 --> 01:37.848
A KID SNEEZED ON ME.
I FELT IT GO IN.

01:37.848 --> 01:40.181
IT LOOKED AROUND,
AND IT SAT DOWN.

01:40.181 --> 01:41.272
WHAT, YOU FELT THAT?

01:41.272 --> 01:42.983
YES, I'VE BEEN
DOING THIS A WHILE.

01:42.983 --> 01:44.355
YOU START
TO DEVELOP A SENSE.

01:44.355 --> 01:46.567
I'VE GOT SEVEN HOURS,
TOPS.

01:46.567 --> 01:50.070
IT SPREADS
BY TOUCHING DOORS, DESKS...

01:50.070 --> 01:51.612
SO LET'S JUST CANCEL.
NO.

01:51.612 --> 01:53.234
1 IN 5,000 BABIES
IS BORN WITHOUT --

01:53.234 --> 01:54.615
WITHOUT A BUTTHOLE,
RIGHT.

01:54.615 --> 01:56.327
WITH A BIRTH DEFECT RESULTING
IN AN IMPERFORATE ANUS.

01:56.327 --> 01:58.078
ALEX,
YOU NEED TO LEARN THIS.
WELL, FINE.

01:58.078 --> 01:59.740
BUT DO I HAVE TO LEARN IT
FROM DR. BUTTHOLE?

01:59.740 --> 02:01.081
DON'T CALL HIM THAT.

02:01.081 --> 02:03.504
DR. LEBACKES IS
A GREAT PEDIATRIC SURGEON

02:03.504 --> 02:05.706
WHO SPECIALIZES
IN ANOPLASTY.

02:05.706 --> 02:07.127
AND YOU HAVEN'T EVEN
MET HIM YET.
OH, I KNOW HIM.

02:07.127 --> 02:08.459
THESE
PRIVATE-PRACTICE DOCS

02:08.459 --> 02:09.880
ARE ONLY ABOUT SEEING
HOW MUCH THEY CAN CHARGE.

02:09.880 --> 02:11.802
HEY, CANCEL
TOMORROW'S PROCEDURES, OKAY?

02:11.802 --> 02:14.014
WHY?
BECAUSE I WILL BE SICK.

02:14.014 --> 02:16.177
OKAY, I'LL PAGE YOU
WHEN I GET A TIME FROM LEBACKES.

02:16.177 --> 02:18.018
JUST TELL ME
WITH YOUR MIND.
UH-HUH.

02:18.018 --> 02:22.102
...ELEVATOR BUTTONS,
PENS, SHARING CUPS.

02:22.102 --> 02:24.975
I FOUND THESE PAYMENT BOOKS
IN A STACK OF MAIL.

02:24.975 --> 02:26.357
THESE ARE
FOR YOUR STUDENT LOANS.

02:26.357 --> 02:27.938
YEAH?
WHAT ABOUT THEM?

02:27.938 --> 02:29.109
HAVE YOU LOOKED AT THEM?

02:29.109 --> 02:30.651
YOU HAVE TO DO SOMETHING
WITH THESE.

02:30.651 --> 02:32.152
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
YOU'RE RIGHT.
LET ME SEE THEM.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.984
...EVEN MONEY.

02:38.038 --> 02:41.081
ALL WE CAN DO IS TRY OUR BEST
TO PREVENT IT FROM SPREADING.

02:41.081 --> 02:42.333
WE'LL ONLY BE
LIKE 15 MINUTES LATE.

02:42.333 --> 02:43.914
OH, WE WOULDN'T BE LATE
AT ALL IF YOU JUST

02:43.914 --> 02:45.456
PUT THE KEY
ON THE HOOK.

02:45.456 --> 02:47.127
I PUT IT BY THE DOOR SO YOU
WOULD ALWAYS KNOW WHERE IT IS.

02:47.127 --> 02:48.789
I KNOW THE HOOK.
I PLAY WITH THE HOOK.

02:48.789 --> 02:50.090
I'M NOT A HOOK GUY.
OH, REAL-- I'M NOT A --

02:50.090 --> 02:52.002
HUH?
I'M NOT A CAN'T-FIND-MY-KEYS
KIND OF GIRL.

02:52.002 --> 02:53.504
MM-HMM. THAT'S WHAT
I'M SAYING, THOUGH, RIGHT?

02:53.504 --> 02:55.005
WHAT?
YOU DO YOU, AND I DO ME.

02:55.005 --> 02:56.217
OKAY.

02:56.217 --> 02:59.560
WELL, YOUR YOU
MAKES ME LATE FOR OUR WORK.

02:59.560 --> 03:01.222
WELL...

03:01.222 --> 03:04.064
BECAUSE ONCE IT'S OUT THERE,
THE INFECTION USUALLY WINS.

03:04.064 --> 03:05.436
Owen:
THERE IS A VIRAL INFECTION

03:05.436 --> 03:07.017
RUNNING RAMPANT
THROUGH THIS HOSPITAL.

03:07.017 --> 03:09.650
IT FEELS LIKE FLU SYMPTOMS,
THEN G.I. STUFF.

03:09.650 --> 03:12.022
OH, SORRY. SORRY.
IT GOES WITHOUT SAYING
THAT SOAP, WATER,

03:12.022 --> 03:13.484
AND HAND SANITIZER
ARE YOUR BEST FRIENDS.

03:13.484 --> 03:15.526
AND IF YOU DO FEEL SICK
AND YOU CAN GO HOME,

03:15.526 --> 03:17.027
THEN GO HOME.

03:17.027 --> 03:19.700
SPREAD THE WORD.
THAT'S ALL FOR NOW.
[ SIREN WAILING ]

03:19.700 --> 03:22.283
BLOW, HONEY,
AND STOP PICKING AT YOUR FACE.

03:22.283 --> 03:24.915
MOM, I CAN BLOW MY OWN NOSE.
I'M PRACTICALLY A TWEEN.

03:24.915 --> 03:28.128
HI, I'M DR. KEPNER.
ARE YOU BRADEN?

03:28.128 --> 03:30.541
YES, THIS IS
OUR LITTLE BRADY BUG.
MOM!

03:30.541 --> 03:31.922
David: SO, DID YOU SPEAK
TO OUR DOCTOR?

03:31.922 --> 03:34.134
I DID. HE SAID
BRADEN HAS S.C.I.D.

03:34.134 --> 03:36.006
BUBBLE BOY DISEASE.
BRADEN. [ CHUCKLES ]

03:36.006 --> 03:37.928
HE KNOWS THAT WE HATE IT
WHEN HE CALLS IT THAT.

03:37.928 --> 03:39.099
AND HE SENT YOU HERE?

03:39.099 --> 03:40.471
YES, HE'S OUT
OF THE COUNTRY, S--

03:40.471 --> 03:41.762
RIGHT,
BUT PATIENTS WITH

03:41.762 --> 03:43.304
SEVERE COMBINED
IMMUNODEFICIENCY SYNDROME

03:43.304 --> 03:44.935
ARE GENERALLY ADVISED
TO STEER CLEAR

03:44.935 --> 03:46.607
OF HIGH-RISK INFECTION AREAS
LIKE A HOSPITAL.

03:46.607 --> 03:47.938
WITHOUT
AN IMMUNE SYSTEM --

03:47.938 --> 03:49.690
WE KNOW, EVEN A COMMON COLD
CAN BE LIFE-THREATENING.

03:49.690 --> 03:51.061
WELL, HE'S ON
ENZYME INJECTIONS,

03:51.061 --> 03:52.813
AND THEY'VE BEEN
WORKING VERY WELL.

03:52.813 --> 03:55.696
AND WE WERE JUST SO WORRIED
AND -- BRADEN. FACE.

03:55.696 --> 03:57.067
I'M NOT PICKING AT IT.
JUST TOUCHING IT.

03:57.067 --> 03:58.739
BRADEN, HOW LONG
HAVE YOU HAD THAT?

03:58.739 --> 04:00.200
THIS ZIT?
I DON'T KNOW.

04:00.200 --> 04:03.364
I'M JUST GONNA KEEP
AN EYE ON IT, OKAY?

04:03.364 --> 04:05.996
GEEZ, WHY NOT JUST DRAW AN ARROW
AND THE WORD "ZIT"?

04:05.996 --> 04:07.247
BRADEN!

04:07.247 --> 04:09.079
LAST NIGHT,
HE GOT CONGESTED,

04:09.079 --> 04:10.711
AND WE THOUGHT HE MIGHT
BE GETTING A SINUS INFECTION,

04:10.711 --> 04:12.252
SO WE CALLED OUR DOCTOR.

04:12.252 --> 04:15.426
AND HE SENT YOU HERE TO GET
I.V.I.G. ANTIBIOTICS AND LABS.

04:15.426 --> 04:16.927
GREAT.
LET'S GET HIM STARTED.

04:16.927 --> 04:19.970
STOP TOUCHING YOUR FACE!
STOP TOUCHING YOUR FACE!

04:19.970 --> 04:22.593
ROSS, YOU'RE ON CARDIO.
WILSON, NEURO.

04:22.593 --> 04:24.595
EDWARDS, YOU'RE ON GENERAL
WITH ME AND GREY --

04:24.595 --> 04:25.806
CROHN'S PERFORATION.

04:25.806 --> 04:27.267
YES!
UH, WARREN, PIT.

04:27.267 --> 04:28.389
OUT SICK.
UH, CAMPBELL.

04:28.389 --> 04:30.060
OH, CAMPBELL'S
OUT SICK, TOO.

04:30.060 --> 04:32.563
A THIRD OF US ARE DOWN
WITH A STOMACH-BUG THING.

04:32.563 --> 04:34.024
ACTUALLY, SIR,
I'M GOING HOME SICK.

04:34.024 --> 04:36.317
MURPHY, DOCTORS AREN'T SICK.
PATIENTS ARE SICK.

04:36.317 --> 04:38.198
THAT'S WHY
THERE ARE DOCTORS.

04:38.198 --> 04:40.110
LOOK, UNSPOKEN RULE,
PEOPLE --

04:40.110 --> 04:42.032
SURGEON STAYS HOME,
PATIENT SUFFERS,

04:42.032 --> 04:44.575
AS WELL AS THE DOCTORS
WHO HAVE TO COVER FOR YOU.

04:44.575 --> 04:45.956
YOU DON'T STAY HOME.

04:45.956 --> 04:47.408
YOU PUSH THROUGH.

04:47.408 --> 04:48.619
ALL RIGHT.

04:48.619 --> 04:50.000
WILSON, PIT.

04:50.000 --> 04:51.291
EDWARDS, NEURO.

04:51.291 --> 04:52.963
MURPHY, YOU'RE WITH ME AND GREY.
LET'S GO.

04:52.963 --> 04:54.124
YES, SIR.

04:54.124 --> 04:55.586
IF IT'S
AN UNSPOKEN RULE,

04:55.586 --> 04:57.127
THEN WHY DID HE
JUST TELL US ABOUT IT?

04:57.127 --> 04:59.009
OH, YOU'RE JUST PISSED
'CAUSE YOU ALREADY LOST THE BET.

04:59.009 --> 05:00.631
WHAT BET?

05:00.631 --> 05:02.132
THE BET WHEREIN
THE FIRST ONE OF US

05:02.132 --> 05:04.094
TO FALL DUE
TO ILLNESS TODAY

05:04.094 --> 05:06.096
HAS TO BE SWAP MONKEY
FOR A WEEK.

05:06.096 --> 05:07.688
WHAT'S SWAP MONKEY?

05:07.688 --> 05:09.269
Jo: ALL NEXT WEEK, ONE OF US
DOESN'T LIKE OUR SERVICE,

05:09.269 --> 05:11.982
WE CAN TRADE
WITH THE SWAP MONKEY,

05:11.982 --> 05:13.233
AND THEY CAN'T REFUSE.

05:13.233 --> 05:15.195
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]
YOU JUST MADE THIS UP.

05:15.195 --> 05:16.857
WELL, THAT DOESN'T MAKE IT
ANY LESS AMAZING.
YEAH.

05:16.857 --> 05:18.399
[ SIGHS ] I'M IN.

05:18.399 --> 05:19.940
GETTING SICK
ISN'T EVEN AN OPTION FOR ME.

05:19.940 --> 05:21.492
IT'S A HUGE DAY
FOR THE CONDUIT TRIAL.

05:21.492 --> 05:23.203
I CAN'T LOSE.
NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.

05:23.203 --> 05:25.406
YOU CAN'T LOSE
BECAUSE LEAH ALREADY DID!

05:25.406 --> 05:27.828
I DID NOT LOSE.
I AM NOT GOING DOWN.

05:27.828 --> 05:29.910
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO'S GONNA BE...
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

05:32.002 --> 05:34.004
OH, GOD.

05:34.004 --> 05:36.046
WHERE IS SHE GOING?

05:36.046 --> 05:37.257
BATHROOM.
[ GASPS ]

05:37.257 --> 05:38.459
DEAD MAN WALKING!

05:38.459 --> 05:39.840
[ PEOPLE COUGHING ]

05:39.840 --> 05:41.672
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

05:41.672 --> 05:44.094
HEY!

05:44.094 --> 05:46.306
HEY.

05:46.306 --> 05:48.889
EXCUSE ME.
SORRY?

05:48.889 --> 05:50.350
I'VE BEEN WAITING
A LONG TIME.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.352
OH, UH, I SEE.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.934
THANK YOU
FOR YOUR PATIENCE.

05:53.934 --> 05:56.186
NO, NO, THIS ISN'T PATIENCE.
I CAN'T MOVE MY MOUTH.

05:56.186 --> 05:57.438
SAY WHAT?

05:57.438 --> 05:59.530
HE SAYS HE'S A DUMMY
WHO CUT HIMSELF COMPOSTING

05:59.530 --> 06:02.072
AND REFUSED TO GET A
TETANUS SHOT OR GET IT CLEANED.

06:02.072 --> 06:03.113
I'M HIS BROTHER, ABRAHAM.

06:03.113 --> 06:04.905
LOGAN, THEY DIDN'T HAVE
COCONUT WATER.

06:04.905 --> 06:06.537
ALL THEY HAD WAS SODA.
NO!

06:06.537 --> 06:08.659
THAT STUFF'S POISON.
GET OUT OF HERE.

06:08.659 --> 06:10.080
THERE IT IS.
EVERYTHING'S POISON.

06:10.080 --> 06:11.992
THIS LOOKS
LIKE RICTUS SARDONICUS,

06:11.992 --> 06:13.624
CAUSING YOUR MUSCLES
TO TIGHTEN.

06:13.624 --> 06:15.706
AND WITH A CUT LIKE THAT,
TETANUS IS MORE THAN LIKELY.

06:15.706 --> 06:17.498
SO I'M GONNA
RE-CLEAN THE WOUND,

06:17.498 --> 06:18.959
AND I STRONGLY SUGGEST

06:18.959 --> 06:22.132
TETANUS TOXOID
AND IMMUNOGLOBULIN.
SEE, BUDDY?

06:22.132 --> 06:23.634
YOU TAKE THE MEDS,
WE GET OUT OF HERE,

06:23.634 --> 06:25.055
AND YOU CAN GET RIGHT BACK TO
SUCKLING MOTHER NATURE'S TEAT.

06:25.055 --> 06:26.557
NO, IT'S POISON.
I CAN ASSURE YOU
THAT IT ISN'T.

06:26.557 --> 06:29.890
POISON!

06:29.890 --> 06:31.181
YOU WANT TO HIT HIM,
OR CAN I?

06:32.102 --> 06:35.275
IVY McNEIL, 15,
END-STAGE HEART FAILURE

06:35.275 --> 06:37.017
DUE TO DILATED
CARDIOMYOPATHY.

06:37.017 --> 06:38.729
SHE'S BEEN
ON THE TRANSPLANT LIST

06:38.729 --> 06:40.020
FOR APPROXIMATELY
FOUR MONTHS.

06:40.020 --> 06:41.782
UNTIL TODAY, RIGHT?
Cristina: LOOKS LIKE IT.

06:41.782 --> 06:43.984
THE DONOR'S HEART'S
BEING EVALUATED RIGHT NOW,

06:43.984 --> 06:46.527
AND IF ALL GOES WELL,
WE SHOULD BE TAKING YOU UP SOON.

06:46.527 --> 06:48.619
Sabine:
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.
[ LAUGHS ]

06:48.619 --> 06:50.080
WHERE ARE
THE REST OF YOU?

06:50.080 --> 06:52.032
IT'S USUALLY
MUCH NOISIER.
I KNOW.

06:52.032 --> 06:55.125
IVY'S LITTLE SISTER CAUGHT
THE FLU BUG THAT'S GOING AROUND,

06:55.125 --> 06:56.627
SO JON'S HOME
WITH HER AND LINK.

06:56.627 --> 06:59.920
THEY TELL YOU
IN THOSE COUNSELING SESSIONS

06:59.920 --> 07:02.002
NOT TO GET YOUR HOPES UP.
DO YOU REALLY THINK --

07:02.002 --> 07:03.133
I SAW THE REPORT
ON THE HEART,

07:03.133 --> 07:05.175
AND I HAVE
A VERY GOOD FEELING.

07:05.175 --> 07:06.717
[ CHUCKLES ] YAY.

07:06.717 --> 07:08.348
YAY!

07:08.348 --> 07:09.139
YAY!

07:09.139 --> 07:10.551
CRAP.

07:10.551 --> 07:12.352
CRAP. I KNOW.
HEY, WHAT'S WRONG?

07:12.352 --> 07:15.015
A DONOR HEART JUST SHOWED UP
FOR MY CARDIOMYOPATHY KID.

07:15.015 --> 07:16.316
HELP ME OUT
WITH WHY THAT'S BAD.

07:16.316 --> 07:17.437
IT'S JUST BAD TIMING.

07:17.437 --> 07:18.649
TODAY'S DAY 30 OF RECOVERY

07:18.649 --> 07:20.060
FOR OUR
CONDUIT TRIAL PATIENTS --

07:20.060 --> 07:21.942
THE LAST DAY FOR OUR REPORT
TO THE N.I.H.,

07:21.942 --> 07:24.274
WHICH WILL INFORM YOUR
HARPER AVERY CONSIDERATION.

07:24.274 --> 07:26.527
I -- YOU SAID THAT.
I DIDN'T. BUT YES.

07:26.527 --> 07:29.119
I PLAN ON SPENDING ALL DAY
WITH THE CONDUIT KIDS

07:29.119 --> 07:31.662
TO ENSURE WE END UP
WITH THE MOST OPTIMAL RESULTS.

07:31.662 --> 07:33.664
AND INSTEAD, YOU HAVE TO SAVE
THE LIFE OF A LITTLE GIRL.

07:33.664 --> 07:35.125
THAT SUCKS.
OH, I KNOW.

07:35.125 --> 07:36.206
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

07:36.206 --> 07:37.918
OH, YOU'RE BEING
FACETIOUS.
YEAH.

07:37.918 --> 07:40.751
HE'S RIGHT.

07:40.751 --> 07:43.003
AND IT WOULD BE NICE TO GET BACK
INTO THE O.R., WON'T IT?

07:43.003 --> 07:44.294
OH, NO.

07:44.294 --> 07:46.386
YES. YOU STAY
WITH THE TRIAL PATIENTS.

07:46.386 --> 07:47.928
KEEP THEM SAFE AND WARM.

07:47.928 --> 07:49.800
TODAY'S NUMBERS HAVE GOT TO BE
THE BEST THEY'VE EVER BEEN.

07:49.800 --> 07:51.141
THERE ARE NURSES
THAT CAN --

07:51.141 --> 07:52.933
SHANE, THERE'S A BUG
GOING AROUND THIS HOSPITAL.

07:52.933 --> 07:55.095
IF ONE OF THOSE PATIENTS'
CONDUITS GETS INFECTED,

07:55.095 --> 07:56.096
THE TRIAL DIES.

07:56.096 --> 07:57.688
I'LL JOIN YOU
WHEN I'M DONE.

07:57.688 --> 08:01.602
THIS TRIAL
IS MY BABY, SHANE.

08:02.442 --> 08:04.314
DON'T LET MY BABY DIE.

08:06.156 --> 08:07.988
POOR GUY CONKED OUT.

08:07.988 --> 08:09.279
HEY, CHAMP.
DOCTOR'S HERE.

08:09.279 --> 08:10.991
HEY, BRADEN,
YOU FEELING ANY BETTER?

08:10.991 --> 08:12.953
I DON'T KNOW.
STILL A LITTLE STUFFY.

08:12.953 --> 08:15.916
BUT...YEAH,
MAYBE A LITTLE BETTER.

08:15.916 --> 08:17.077
April: OKAY, BRADEN,
WE'RE GONNA MOVE YOU

08:17.077 --> 08:19.620
TO SOMEPLACE
A LITTLE MORE COMFY, OKAY?

08:19.620 --> 08:21.081
[ TELEPHONE RINGING,
PEOPLE COUGHING ]

08:21.081 --> 08:24.885
We need to move my patient
into isolation right now.

08:24.885 --> 08:27.177
[ COUGHING AND SNEEZING ]

08:29.389 --> 08:31.091
[ SIGHS ]

08:42.062 --> 08:44.565
SO EVERY TIME YOU GO
INTO BRADEN'S ROOM,

08:44.565 --> 08:47.738
YOU WILL PUT ON A FRESH GOWN,
GLOVES, AND MASK.

08:47.738 --> 08:49.950
RIGHT. EVERY TIME.
YEAH.

08:49.950 --> 08:53.614
THE LUMP ON BRADEN'S HEAD IS
A RAPIDLY GROWING INFECTION.

08:53.614 --> 08:55.285
WE JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE
HE DOESN'T GET ANY MORE.

08:55.285 --> 08:56.787
BUT HE'S BEEN
TAKING THE ENZYME.

08:56.787 --> 08:58.288
IT'S SUPPOSED TO STOP THIS KIND
OF THING FROM HAPPENING.

08:58.288 --> 09:00.581
HIS LABS SHOW
HIS T-CELL COUNT IS ZERO,

09:00.581 --> 09:03.373
WHICH MEANS HE'S DEVELOPED
ANTIBODIES TO THE ENZYME

09:03.373 --> 09:04.755
AND IT'S
NO LONGER WORKING.

09:04.755 --> 09:07.718
HE'S HIGHLY SUSCEPTIBLE
TO ALL TYPES OF INFECTION.

09:07.718 --> 09:11.011
HAVE YOU CONSIDERED
A BONE-MARROW TRANSPLANT?

09:11.011 --> 09:13.133
WE TRIED TO FIND THE MATCH
RIGHT AFTER HE WAS BORN,

09:13.133 --> 09:14.675
BUT ETHNIC DONORS
ARE SO HARD TO FIND.

09:14.675 --> 09:17.728
THEY RECOMMENDED
THE ENZYME INSTEAD.

09:17.728 --> 09:19.309
IT'S BEEN WORKING.

09:19.309 --> 09:21.561
IT WAS WORKING.

09:30.611 --> 09:31.612
YOU READY?

09:31.612 --> 09:32.993
Teresa: I'M READY.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.697
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

09:36.697 --> 09:38.699
HEY, CHAMP.
BRADY BUG!

09:38.699 --> 09:40.871
HI, SWEETIE. OHH.

09:40.871 --> 09:42.663
MOM.

09:42.663 --> 09:44.755
[ SIGHS ]

09:44.755 --> 09:46.837
OHH. BABY.

09:48.508 --> 09:50.711
YEAH, THIS IS A U.S. PROJECT,
BUT I BELIEVE OUR --

09:50.711 --> 09:52.592
OUR BEST APPROACH
IS TO OPEN OUR DOORS

09:52.592 --> 09:55.305
TO WELCOME YOUR PARTICIPATION.

09:55.305 --> 09:58.138
YOU KNOW, WE'RE TRYING TO GAIN
A COMPREHENSIVE UNDERSTANDING

09:58.138 --> 10:01.642
OF THE MOST COMPLEX OBJECT
IN THE WORLD -- OUR BRAIN.

10:01.642 --> 10:05.435
WE ARE WILLING
TO TAKE EVERY GREAT MIND

10:05.435 --> 10:08.228
WE CAN ACCESS TO DO IT --
YOUR MINDS.

10:08.228 --> 10:09.690
WE WELCOME YOU.

10:09.690 --> 10:11.611
THANK YOU FOR JOINING US.

10:11.611 --> 10:13.443
THAT WAS GREAT.
YOU DID A GOOD JOB.

10:13.443 --> 10:14.695
[ BABY COOS ]
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

10:14.695 --> 10:16.787
I WENT UP TO DAYCARE
TO FIND MY SON MISSING.

10:16.787 --> 10:18.789
YEAH, I NEEDED AN AUDIENCE.
LOOK, SIT DOWN.

10:18.789 --> 10:20.701
LET ME GO OVER THIS AGAIN
WITH YOU, OKAY?
OH, NO, NO, NO.

10:20.701 --> 10:23.123
I'VE HEARD THAT SPEECH SO
MANY TIMES I COULD DO IT MYSELF.

10:23.123 --> 10:24.795
STOP BORING OUR SON.
IS IT BORING?

10:24.795 --> 10:25.956
I HAVE 50 SCIENTISTS

10:25.956 --> 10:27.547
FROM AROUND THE WORLD
COMING HERE TODAY.

10:27.547 --> 10:29.169
IT'S GOT TO BE CHARMING.
IT'S A BIG DEAL.

10:29.169 --> 10:30.510
I KNOW IT'S A BIG DEAL,

10:30.510 --> 10:32.592
WHICH IS WHY I WILL
GET OUT OF YOUR WAY.

10:32.592 --> 10:34.384
MM-HMM.
MM-HMM.
MM-HMM.

10:34.384 --> 10:35.756
[ BABY COOS ]

10:35.756 --> 10:38.468
AND I'M TAKING MY SON WITH ME
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT

10:38.468 --> 10:39.970
HIS FIRST WORD
TO BE HYPOTHALAMUS.

10:39.970 --> 10:41.722
THERE ARE
WORSE FIRST WORDS.

10:41.722 --> 10:43.103
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:43.103 --> 10:44.685
UH...

10:44.685 --> 10:46.436
THANK YOU.

10:46.436 --> 10:47.858
GOOD NEWS.

10:47.858 --> 10:50.110
THE HEART CHECKED OUT OKAY
AND IS EN ROUTE.

10:50.110 --> 10:51.692
TIME TO GO TO THE O.R.
THANK GOD.

10:51.692 --> 10:53.113
MOM, YOU'LL CALL DAD?

10:53.113 --> 10:54.484
TELL HIM TO E-MAIL MR. MOSS

10:54.484 --> 10:56.236
AND GET THE APPLICATION
FOR STUDENT COUNCIL.

10:56.236 --> 10:58.238
SIGN-UPS HAVE
ALREADY BEEN OUT FOR A WEEK.

11:00.120 --> 11:01.121
MOM?

11:02.122 --> 11:03.954
JUST GIVE ME
A KISS FIRST.

11:06.046 --> 11:08.208
I'M GONNA BE RIGHT HERE
WHEN YOU WAKE UP, OKAY?

11:08.208 --> 11:10.050
I LOVE YOU.

11:14.845 --> 11:16.676
WHEN WE'RE FINISHED
WITH THE SURGERY,

11:16.676 --> 11:17.718
I'LL COME UPDATE YOU.

11:17.718 --> 11:18.759
OKAY, THANK YOU.

11:23.563 --> 11:25.565
[ SIGHS ]

11:25.565 --> 11:28.308
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
[ SNIFFS ]

11:28.308 --> 11:30.310
HEY.

11:30.310 --> 11:33.904
YEAH,
THEY JUST TOOK HER UP.

11:33.904 --> 11:37.117
HOW'S FRANKIE?

11:37.117 --> 11:39.529
YEAH, I'M OKAY...

11:41.872 --> 11:45.746
[ Voice breaking ] SORT OF.

11:45.746 --> 11:48.498
YEAH, I WISH
YOU WERE HERE, TOO.

11:48.498 --> 11:50.290
OKAY.

11:50.290 --> 11:52.292
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

11:52.292 --> 11:54.004
[ SIGHS ]

11:56.006 --> 11:57.507
WHOO, HEY.

11:57.507 --> 11:59.549
I'M GONNA NEED YOU TO GET
SOFIA TO SCHOOL IN THE MORNING

11:59.549 --> 12:00.640
'CAUSE I'M GONNA
BE HOME SICK.

12:00.640 --> 12:01.762
THIS AGAIN.
OH.

12:01.762 --> 12:03.053
NO, NO,
THIS IS HER SUPERPOWER.

12:03.053 --> 12:04.604
SHE LOOKS FINE NOW,
BUT --
SHE IS FINE.

12:04.604 --> 12:06.516
NO, I'M THINKING IT'S GONNA BE
ABOUT THREE DAYS.

12:06.516 --> 12:07.978
SO YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU SHOULD CANCEL DINNER

12:07.978 --> 12:08.979
WITH PAM AND THEM, TOO.

12:08.979 --> 12:10.270
OH, NO, CAN YOU CALL?
HMM?

12:10.270 --> 12:11.521
I-I DON'T EVEN HAVE
A RESIDENT TODAY,

12:11.521 --> 12:12.612
AND EVERYONE'S OUT
WITH THE PLAGUE, SO...

12:12.612 --> 12:13.814
SPEAKING OF CANCELING,

12:13.814 --> 12:15.695
ARE YOU SURE DR. BUTTHOLE'S
GONNA BE HERE?

12:15.695 --> 12:16.857
[ SCOFFS ]
HE'S ALREADY LATE.

12:16.857 --> 12:18.618
DR. BUTTHOLE
HAS ARRIVED.

12:18.618 --> 12:20.240
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
AH!

12:20.240 --> 12:21.661
I GET THAT A LOT.

12:21.661 --> 12:23.954
ALSO, DR. POOP CHUTE,
DR. REAR GEAR, DR. RUMP CHUMP.

12:23.954 --> 12:25.956
BUT MY FAVORITE --
THE SPHINCTER FAIRY.

12:25.956 --> 12:27.868
MY FRIENDS
CALL ME OLIVER,

12:27.868 --> 12:29.709
AND YOU LOOK RADIANT,
AS ALWAYS.

12:29.709 --> 12:31.371
OH, IT'S REALLY NICE
TO SEE YOU, OLLIE.

12:31.371 --> 12:32.923
YEAH, I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T -- I-I-I WASN'T --

12:32.923 --> 12:34.504
OH, NO OFFENSE TAKEN.

12:34.504 --> 12:36.216
I'LL JUST CRY MYSELF
TO SLEEP TONIGHT

12:36.216 --> 12:37.677
ON MY PILES
AND PILES OF MONEY.

12:37.677 --> 12:39.179
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
WE READY?

12:39.179 --> 12:41.972
[ Laughing ]
YES. LET'S GO.

12:41.972 --> 12:43.553
HEY, BRADEN MORRIS
IS HERE?

12:43.553 --> 12:45.185
HE WAS MY PATIENT
A FEW YEARS AGO.

12:45.185 --> 12:46.766
WHAT'S GOING ON?
HIS MEDS STOPPED WORKING.

12:46.766 --> 12:48.688
HE'S GOT
ACUTE FRONTAL SINUSITIS.

12:48.688 --> 12:50.060
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
IT'S SPREADING FAST.

12:50.060 --> 12:51.391
[ DOOR OPENS ]

12:51.391 --> 12:53.773
WELL,
IT'S A POTTS PUFFY TUMOR.

12:53.773 --> 12:56.817
HE SHOULD GET TO SURGERY
RIGHT AWAY, GET IT DRAINED.

12:56.817 --> 12:58.608
MAKE SURE
IT DOESN'T SPREAD AND --

12:58.608 --> 12:59.860
April: YOU LOOK HORRIBLE.

12:59.860 --> 13:01.401
YEAH, CORRECT.
YOU LOOK HORRIBLE.

13:01.401 --> 13:03.573
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU?
OH, NOTHING.

13:03.573 --> 13:05.365
IT'S -- MY STOMACH'S
A LITTLE SCREWY. I'M FINE.

13:05.365 --> 13:08.038
GONNA, UM,
GO BOOK AN O.R., THOUGH.

13:08.038 --> 13:09.169
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

13:09.169 --> 13:10.500
THE BEST THING YOU CAN DO
FOR THIS KID

13:10.500 --> 13:11.501
IS TO BE NOWHERE NEAR HIM.

13:11.501 --> 13:12.622
BECAUSE
YOU LOOK HORRIBLE.

13:12.622 --> 13:14.624
YEAH, I CAN DRAIN
A POTTS PUFFY TUMOR.

13:14.624 --> 13:16.086
GO HOME.
YEAH, YOU SHOULD GO HOME.

13:16.086 --> 13:17.297
YOU NEED TO --
I'M FINE.

13:17.297 --> 13:18.628
OKAY? I CAN TAKE CARE
OF MYSELF.

13:18.628 --> 13:20.090
OHH.
MM-HMM.

13:20.090 --> 13:21.421
MAYBE I WILL.

13:21.421 --> 13:22.472
YES, YOU SHOULD GO HOME,

13:22.472 --> 13:24.724
PUT ON SOME
GOOD, FLUFFY SOCKS.

13:24.724 --> 13:26.096
OH, THERE'S SOUP
IN THE PANTRY,

13:26.096 --> 13:27.597
AND JUST GO GET IN THE SHOWER
AND SIT IN IT TO --

13:27.597 --> 13:29.729
APRIL!
I KNOW HOW TO BE SICK.

13:31.231 --> 13:32.642
I'M NOT EVEN SICK.

13:32.642 --> 13:34.564
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

13:34.564 --> 13:36.486
JUST TRYING TO HELP HIM.

13:36.486 --> 13:39.239
WELL, LET'S GO HELP HIM.
[ SIGHS ]

13:39.239 --> 13:41.781
MR. GORDER, YOUR LABS LOOK GREAT
AND YOUR EKG IS CLEAR,

13:41.781 --> 13:43.243
SO WE'RE GONNA BE
SENDING YOU

13:43.243 --> 13:45.115
UP TO THE O.R.
IN A LITTLE BIT, OKAY?

13:45.115 --> 13:47.407
YEAH, SOUNDS GOOD.
UH, NERVOUS?

13:47.407 --> 13:48.788
A LITTLE BIT, YEAH.

13:48.788 --> 13:50.040
HOW ABOUT IF DR. MURPHY

13:50.040 --> 13:51.872
TAKES YOU THROUGH
THE PROCEDURE ONE MORE TIME?

13:51.872 --> 13:53.213
MURPHY?

13:55.085 --> 13:57.757
UH, SHE MIGHT BE ASLEEP.

13:57.757 --> 14:01.091
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

14:02.172 --> 14:03.673
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

14:03.673 --> 14:04.965
SHE'S NOT ASLEEP.

14:04.965 --> 14:06.266
Leah: YEAH, NO, NO.

14:06.266 --> 14:09.469
I...WAS JUST GOING OVER
YOUR CASE IN MY HEAD,

14:09.469 --> 14:11.731
AND NOW I'LL GO OVER IT
WITH YOU.

14:11.731 --> 14:14.644
YOU HAVE
A WALLED-OFF ABSCESS.

14:14.644 --> 14:16.856
SO WE'LL CLEAN OUT
THE PUSS

14:16.856 --> 14:18.858
AND, UM, RESECT A PORTION
OF YOUR BOWEL.

14:18.858 --> 14:21.571
AND I'LL STILL BE ABLE
TO POOP JUST FINE?

14:21.571 --> 14:22.862
YES, SIR.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.444
THAT'S THE PLAN.

14:27.197 --> 14:29.869
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

14:29.869 --> 14:31.661
JUST CALL
ALL THE COLLEGES.

14:31.661 --> 14:33.623
SEE IF ANYBODY THERE
CAN SPEAK IT.

14:33.623 --> 14:35.255
Woman: RIGHT AWAY,
DR. SHEPHERD.

14:35.255 --> 14:36.706
ARE YOU OKAY?

14:36.706 --> 14:38.258
UH, IF YOU CAN
SPEAK ESTONIAN.

14:38.258 --> 14:39.709
MY TRANSLATOR CALLED
IN SICK.

14:39.709 --> 14:41.591
YOU DON'T LOOK GOOD.
ARE YOU GETTING THIS THING?

14:41.591 --> 14:42.923
I DON'T GET SICK.
IT'S AN UNSPOKEN RULE.

14:42.923 --> 14:44.094
SPOKEN. TWICE TODAY.

14:44.094 --> 14:45.305
YEAH, WELL, EVEN IF I WERE
GONNA GET SICK,

14:45.305 --> 14:46.556
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN
TODAY.

14:46.556 --> 14:48.138
MURPHY, YOU LOOK AWFUL.
I'M PUSHING THROUGH.

14:48.138 --> 14:49.769
YOU KNOW,
GET AWAY FROM ME.

14:52.102 --> 14:53.773
Oh, wow. He's here.

14:53.773 --> 14:55.355
WHO'S HERE?
He came.

14:55.355 --> 14:56.816
IS THAT
GERHARDT STRAUSS?

14:56.816 --> 14:58.438
GERHARDT STRAUSS IS COMING
TO YOUR THING?

14:58.438 --> 14:59.729
I TOLD YOU, MEREDITH,
IT'S A BIG DEAL.

14:59.729 --> 15:02.152
[ German accent ] AHH.
DR. DEREK SHEPHERD.

15:02.152 --> 15:03.573
IT IS A PLEASURE
TO MEET YOU.

15:03.573 --> 15:05.195
DR. STRAUSS.
PLEASURE'S ALL MINE.

15:05.195 --> 15:06.366
UH, THANK YOU FOR COMING.

15:06.366 --> 15:07.787
I WAS, UH,
INTRIGUED, SHEPHERD.

15:07.787 --> 15:09.239
YOUR PROJECT WAS THE TALK

15:09.239 --> 15:11.411
OF THE E.U.
NEUROSCIENCE CONFERENCE.

15:11.411 --> 15:12.742
OH.

15:12.742 --> 15:14.534
MOSTLY, PEOPLE WERE WONDERING
WHETHER IT WAS

15:14.534 --> 15:18.668
A SERIOUS EFFORT OR JUST
A P.R. STUNT FOR YOUR PRESIDENT.

15:18.668 --> 15:20.840
WELL, YOU'LL FELL MORE CONFIDENT
AFTER THE PRESENTATION.

15:20.840 --> 15:23.463
WELL, I HAVE NO DOUBT THAT YOU
WILL CHARM AND DAZZLE US.

15:23.463 --> 15:25.805
I JUST HOPE
THAT IT IS NOT A BIG, UM...

15:25.805 --> 15:28.388
WHAT IS THE PHRASE
YOU USE?

15:28.388 --> 15:29.639
UM...
HYPE?

15:29.639 --> 15:30.760
NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO.
FLASH OVER SUBSTANCE?

15:30.760 --> 15:32.762
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
UM, UH, COM--

15:32.762 --> 15:34.684
COMPLETE WASTE OF MY TIME.

15:34.684 --> 15:36.726
HMM.
YES.

15:36.726 --> 15:38.108
I LOOK FORWARD TO IT.

15:38.108 --> 15:39.439
OH, GOOD. THANK YOU.
YEAH.

15:39.439 --> 15:41.821
[ SIGHS ]
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

15:41.821 --> 15:43.443
SURE YOU FEEL OKAY?

15:43.443 --> 15:45.365
MM-HMM.

15:45.365 --> 15:47.617
[ BEEPS ]
98.9.

15:47.617 --> 15:48.989
YOU'RE CLEAR.

15:48.989 --> 15:52.412
NEXT.

15:52.412 --> 15:54.204
IS THIS
REALLY NECESSARY?

15:54.204 --> 15:55.996
[ BEEPS ]
WHOA. 100.7.

15:55.996 --> 15:58.078
I'M SORRY.
I CAN'T LET YOU IN.
THAT'S BARELY A FEVER.

15:58.078 --> 15:59.289
MA'AM,
YOUR DAUGHTER'S TRYING

15:59.289 --> 16:00.670
TO HEAL
FROM HER CONDUIT SURGERY.

16:00.670 --> 16:02.542
WE DON'T WANT ANYTHING TO
INTERFERE WITH THAT, RIGHT?

16:02.542 --> 16:04.134
REST UP.
LOTS OF FLUIDS.

16:04.134 --> 16:06.046
EXCUSE ME.
OH,
GET AWAY FROM HERE.

16:06.046 --> 16:07.467
NO, COME ON.
THE PIT'S A HOT ZONE.

16:07.467 --> 16:09.089
IF I STAY DOWN THERE,
I'M GONNA GET SICK. COME ON.

16:09.089 --> 16:11.051
[ SNIFFLES,
CLEARS THROAT ]

16:11.051 --> 16:12.762
OKAY,
YOU SHOULD GO HOME.

16:12.762 --> 16:13.803
NO,
I'M PUSHING THROUGH.

16:13.803 --> 16:14.934
WELL, PUSH THROUGH
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

16:14.934 --> 16:16.266
YOU'RE TOO CLOSE
TO MY PATIENTS.

16:16.266 --> 16:17.857
AND YOU HAVE A SHEEN.

16:17.857 --> 16:19.149
OH, ARE YOU ENJOYING
THAT COFFEE?

16:19.149 --> 16:20.940
BECAUSE I DID WHEN I TOOK

16:20.940 --> 16:22.772
A BIG SIP OF IT
IN THE LOUNGE THIS MORNING.

16:22.772 --> 16:24.984
YOU DIDN'T.
DID I?

16:24.984 --> 16:26.736
[ LAUGHS ]

16:26.736 --> 16:28.158
I DON'T LIKE THIS
AT ALL.

16:28.158 --> 16:30.160
HIS ABDOMEN'S RIGID.
HE'S FEVERISH.

16:30.160 --> 16:33.493
SIR, IT'S YOUR CHOICE NOT
TO ACCEPT THE TETANUS TOXOID,

16:33.493 --> 16:36.206
BUT YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT
FULL-BLOWN TETANUS CAN KILL YOU.

16:36.206 --> 16:37.617
YOUR RESPIRATORY MUSCLES
WILL SPASM.

16:37.617 --> 16:40.210
YOU WON'T BE ABLE
TO BREATHE.
YOU'RE A TEAR-DONGER!

16:40.210 --> 16:41.751
HERE WE GO.

16:41.751 --> 16:43.673
WHAT DID HE CALL ME?
A FEAR-MONGER.

16:43.673 --> 16:45.465
HE THINKS BIG PHARMA
LAY ON SCARY STATISTICS

16:45.465 --> 16:47.257
IN ORDER TO GET PEOPLE
TO BUY IN TO THEIR POISONS.

16:47.257 --> 16:49.629
THEY DO.
I AM NOT BIG PHARMA.

16:49.629 --> 16:51.471
I AM YOUR DOCTOR,
AND I'M TRYING --

16:51.471 --> 16:52.802
YOU'RE THEIR HUT-HETT.
WHAT?!

16:52.802 --> 16:54.474
I AM NOBODY'S PUPPET!

16:54.474 --> 16:55.805
AND I'M TRYING TO KEEP YOU
FROM GETTING SICKER

16:55.805 --> 16:57.057
THAN YOU'VE ALREADY
MADE YOURSELF, SO --

16:57.057 --> 16:58.848
[ GROANS ]
OH, MY GOD! OKAY, OKAY.

16:58.848 --> 17:01.311
LOGAN, I'M RUNNING OUT OF WAYS
OF SAYING, "I TOLD YOU SO."

17:01.311 --> 17:03.193
I GOT YOU. OH, MY GOD!
[ BONE CRACKS ]

17:03.193 --> 17:05.024
OH, MY GOD!
[ SCREAMS ] OH, GOD!

17:05.024 --> 17:06.736
OH, MY GOD!
OHH, GOD!

17:06.736 --> 17:07.697
OH, MY GOD! OH, MY GOD!

17:13.743 --> 17:14.914
[ GEORGE CLINTON'S
"ATOMIC DOG" PLAYS ]

17:14.914 --> 17:16.416
YEAH, THIS IS THE STORY
OF A FAMOUS DOG.

17:16.416 --> 17:19.249
YOU KNOW, THEY TEACH
DR. LEBACKES' TECHNIQUE

17:19.249 --> 17:20.620
IN MED SCHOOL NOW.

17:20.620 --> 17:22.542
DR. ROBBINS,
YOU'RE MAKING ME BLUSH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:22.542 --> 17:24.424
EVERYONE HAS TO HAVE
A SPECIALTY, RIGHT?

17:24.424 --> 17:25.875
AND EVERYBODY HAS
TO POOP.

17:25.875 --> 17:29.379
DO YOU ALWAYS LISTEN TO MUSIC
LIKE THIS DURING SURGERY?

17:29.379 --> 17:30.430
ANYTHING WITH A BEAT.

17:30.430 --> 17:32.092
WE SPEND ENOUGH TIME
HERE AT WORK.

17:32.092 --> 17:33.223
IT OUGHT TO BE FUN,
RIGHT?

17:33.223 --> 17:34.474
AND THE '80s WERE NOTHING
IF NOT FUN.

17:34.474 --> 17:36.015
HEMOCLIP!

17:38.438 --> 17:41.231
I KNOW THIS IS OLD HAT
FOR YOU, OLIVER,

17:41.231 --> 17:43.233
BUT DR. KAREV'S NEVER SEEN
THIS PROCEDURE FIRSTHAND.

17:43.233 --> 17:44.444
YOU WANT
TO WALK HIM THROUGH IT?

17:44.444 --> 17:46.025
OH, GOD. I'M SORRY.

17:46.025 --> 17:47.777
YEAH, UH, KILL THE MUSIC,
WILL YOU?
UH, NO, IT'S COOL.

17:47.777 --> 17:51.191
♪ ATOMIC DOG ♪
IT LOOKS LIKE YOU USED
A POSTERIOR SAGITTAL APPROACH,

17:51.191 --> 17:52.362
AND THEN DIVIDED

17:52.362 --> 17:53.743
THE PARASAGITTAL FIBERS
IN THE MIDLINE.

17:53.743 --> 17:55.955
I'M GUESSING YOU'LL OPEN
THE LEVATOR MUSCLE NEXT?

17:55.955 --> 17:58.198
BOY WONDER
KNOWS HIS STUFF.

17:58.198 --> 18:00.700
YOU THINK I'M THE ONLY ONE
WITH A NICKNAME AROUND HERE?

18:00.700 --> 18:03.333
ALL RIGHT. HERE WE GO.

18:03.333 --> 18:05.415
♪ BOW WOW WOW,
YIPPIE YO, YIPPIE YAY ♪

18:05.415 --> 18:07.547
♪ BOW WOW,
YIPPIE YO, YIPPIE YAY ♪

18:07.547 --> 18:08.798
HUH!

18:08.798 --> 18:10.340
♪ BOW WOW WOW,
YIPPIE YO, YIPPIE YAY ♪

18:10.340 --> 18:12.712
♪ BOW WOW,
YIPPIE YO, YIPPIE YAY ♪
HUH!

18:12.712 --> 18:15.215
YOU WANT ME TO PUT
THE ENTIRE UNIT ON LOCKDOWN...

18:15.215 --> 18:16.426
YES.
...BECAUSE OF THE FLU.

18:16.426 --> 18:17.677
YES.
NO.

18:17.677 --> 18:19.679
ALL DUE RESPECT,
DR. YANG LEFT ME IN CHARGE.

18:19.679 --> 18:22.522
THAT'S CUTE. LISTEN,
I'M IN CHARGE OF THE CCU.

18:22.522 --> 18:24.484
YOU'RE IN CHARGE
OF THREE PATIENTS.

18:24.484 --> 18:27.187
THREE VERY IMPORTANT PATIENTS
WHO NEED PROTECTION FROM THE --

18:27.187 --> 18:28.358
I'M NOT DONE.

18:28.358 --> 18:30.109
YOU CAN PUT YOUR PATIENTS
IN POD 3,

18:30.109 --> 18:32.942
THEN YOU CAN INSTITUTE
WHATEVER KIND OF LOCKDOWN

18:32.942 --> 18:34.324
MAKES YOUR LITTLE HEART
SING.

18:34.324 --> 18:36.786
I HAVE NO NURSES TO SPARE,
SO YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN.

18:36.786 --> 18:38.828
[ COUGHS ]

18:38.828 --> 18:40.790
NOW I'M DONE.
[ COUGHS ]

18:40.790 --> 18:42.542
YOU SHOULD
GET THAT LOOKED AT.

18:42.542 --> 18:44.584
[ COUGHS ]

18:44.584 --> 18:47.167
OH, MAN,
THAT IS A NASTY BREAK.

18:47.167 --> 18:48.838
YOU SEE THIS?

18:48.838 --> 18:51.301
HE HAS AN OLD FRACTURE
THAT NEVER HEALED PROPERLY.

18:51.301 --> 18:52.552
SEE HOW IT'S MAL-ALIGNED?

18:52.552 --> 18:55.175
LEFT THE BONE WEAKER
THAN IT SHOULD HAVE BEEN.

18:55.175 --> 18:57.677
WILSON?

18:57.677 --> 19:00.260
I THINK
THAT THIS IS MY FAULT.

19:00.260 --> 19:01.431
[ SIGHS ]

19:01.431 --> 19:02.972
THE GUY WAS GETTING TO ME
AND I WAS PISSED

19:02.972 --> 19:05.064
AND THEN I WAS JUST TRYING
TO RESTRAIN HIM AND I --

19:05.064 --> 19:07.066
YOU THINK
YOU BROKE HIS ARM?

19:07.066 --> 19:10.270
[ CHUCKLES ] WILSON,
DON'T FLATTER YOURSELF.

19:10.270 --> 19:11.571
TETANUS SPASMS
CAN BE SO INTENSE

19:11.571 --> 19:13.193
THEY'VE BEEN KNOWN
TO OVER-TORQUE AND SNAP BONES.

19:13.193 --> 19:15.034
HE BROKE HIS OWN ARM?

19:15.034 --> 19:16.366
MM-HMM.

19:16.366 --> 19:18.538
BUT WE'RE NOT GONNA BE ABLE
TO REALIGN THE NEW BREAK

19:18.538 --> 19:21.371
WITHOUT RE-BREAKING
THE OLD FRACTURE.

19:21.371 --> 19:23.162
SO YOU
HAVE TO BREAK HIS BONE

19:23.162 --> 19:24.494
IN ORDER TO PUT IT
BACK TOGETHER AGAIN?

19:24.494 --> 19:25.705
NO.

19:25.705 --> 19:26.916
I THINK YOU DO.

19:26.916 --> 19:28.338
I CAN'T DO THAT.

19:28.338 --> 19:29.459
YOU THOUGHT
YOU COULD A SECOND AGO.

19:30.960 --> 19:32.292
[ HEART MONITOR BEEPING ]

19:32.292 --> 19:34.294
April: WHAT'S SO WRONG
WITH WANTING TO HELP SOMEBODY?

19:34.294 --> 19:35.925
IT'S OUR PROFESSION,
FOR GOD'S SAKE.

19:35.925 --> 19:37.257
Miranda: WELL, IF THE MAN
DOESN'T WANT HELP...

19:37.257 --> 19:38.678
HE'S NOT A GOAT!

19:38.678 --> 19:40.470
NO, HE IS NOT.

19:40.470 --> 19:42.101
BOY, IS HE NOT.
[ SIGHS ]

19:42.101 --> 19:44.103
HE DOESN'T NEED TO SEPARATE
FROM THE FLOCK

19:44.103 --> 19:45.645
AND CRAWL
TO THE BACK OF THE BARN

19:45.645 --> 19:47.146
TO TOUGH IT OUT
BY HIMSELF.

19:47.146 --> 19:48.187
I WANT TO HELP.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.149
THEN WELCOME
TO YOUR NEXT 30 YEARS.

19:50.149 --> 19:51.481
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

19:51.481 --> 19:53.693
YOU'RE GONNA WANT
TO HELP HIM.

19:53.693 --> 19:55.365
HE'S GOING TO WANT
TO HELP HIMSELF.

19:55.365 --> 19:57.196
NEITHER OF YOU
IS GOING TO CHANGE.

19:57.196 --> 19:59.118
GET USED
TO THIS ARGUMENT.

19:59.118 --> 20:01.621
MIGHT AS WELL
JUST LET HIM SUFFER?

20:01.621 --> 20:03.032
IF THAT'S WHAT HE WANTS,

20:03.032 --> 20:04.624
GO GET A PEDICURE
AND COUNT YOUR BLESSINGS.

20:04.624 --> 20:07.327
LOOK, THERE'S TWO KINDS
OF MAN SICK --

20:07.327 --> 20:10.039
THE JACKSON KIND
AND THE BEN WARREN KIND.

20:10.039 --> 20:13.423
NOW, WHEN I GET HOME TONIGHT,
DR. BEN WARREN

20:13.423 --> 20:17.096
WILL CALL OUT "MIRANDA"
FROM HIS FETAL POSITION

20:17.096 --> 20:19.469
ON THE COUCH
AND BEG ME FOR SALTINES

20:19.469 --> 20:21.431
AND A WET WASHCLOTH
FOR HIS HEAD.

20:21.431 --> 20:24.344
JACKSON'S CRAWL-AWAY-LIKE-A-GOAT
KIND IS THE GOOD ONE.

20:24.344 --> 20:26.476
OH, GOD, LOOK.

20:26.476 --> 20:28.898
IT'S
CEREBRAL SPINAL FLUID.

20:28.898 --> 20:33.062
OHH, THE ABSCESS HAS PENETRATED
INTO HIS BRAIN SINCE THE C.T.

20:33.062 --> 20:34.814
WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO CALL DR. SHEPHERD.

20:34.814 --> 20:36.025
YEAH.

20:36.025 --> 20:37.617
Derek:
WHETHER YOU BELIEVE, UH,

20:37.617 --> 20:42.031
THAT THIS ULTRASTRUCTURAL
ANALYSIS IS MADE OF...

20:42.031 --> 20:45.164
[ MUNCHING ]

20:45.164 --> 20:50.630
...PHYSIOLOGICAL EXPERIMENT
OR A COMPUTER ALGORITHM,

20:50.630 --> 20:52.922
IT'S SAFE TO SAY
THAT WE CAN ALL AGREE

20:52.922 --> 20:57.877
THAT THE NEURO...CIRCUITS
ARE THE KEY TO...

20:57.877 --> 20:59.969
THOUGHT AND...ACTION.

20:59.969 --> 21:01.140
WHAT ARE YOU EATING?

21:01.140 --> 21:03.303
UH, ONION RINGS.
DO YOU WANT SOME?

21:03.303 --> 21:05.595
TAKE THEM OUTSIDE...
OF THE BUILDING.

21:07.437 --> 21:09.058
I DO BELIEVE
THAT THIS IS --

21:09.058 --> 21:11.230
DR. SHEPHERD,
YOU'RE NEEDED IN O.R. 2.

21:11.230 --> 21:12.652
DR. B--
I AM NOT ON CALL TODAY.

21:12.652 --> 21:14.774
NELSON IS.
NELSON'S OUT SICK
WITH THE STOMACH FLU.

21:14.774 --> 21:16.316
THEN GET AHOLD OF, UH --
GARRISON AND ANDERS, TOO.

21:16.316 --> 21:18.358
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO'S STILL NOT SICK.

21:20.279 --> 21:22.322
UNLESS YOU ARE.

21:22.322 --> 21:23.493
I DON'T GET SICK.

21:26.205 --> 21:28.207
[ PEOPLE COUGHING, SNEEZING ]

21:30.079 --> 21:32.752
Man:
HEADACHE AS WELL.

21:32.752 --> 21:34.293
SWEETIE, I SAID
YOU DIDN'T NEED TO COME.

21:34.293 --> 21:36.085
THEY SAID IT'LL BE
AT LEAST ANOTHER HOUR.

21:36.085 --> 21:37.377
FRANKIE'S GOTTEN WORSE.

21:37.377 --> 21:39.218
SHE'S LIGHT-HEADED
AND REALLY SHORT OF BREATH.

21:39.218 --> 21:40.800
THEY DID AN X-RAY.

21:40.800 --> 21:42.552
NO, JON, IT'S JUST THE FLU.
LOOK AROUND. EVERYBODY HAS IT.

21:42.552 --> 21:44.594
YOU SHOULD HAVE STAYED HOME.
NOW LINK IS GONNA GET IT.

21:44.594 --> 21:46.516
HONEY, SHE WAS
COUGHING UP PINK STUFF.

21:46.516 --> 21:48.307
YOUR HUSBAND
MADE THE RIGHT CALL.

21:48.307 --> 21:50.269
IT IS MORE
THAN JUST FLU.

21:50.269 --> 21:53.813
I'M AFRAID FANCESCA
HAS CARDIOMYOPATHY.

21:53.813 --> 21:55.485
WHAT?

21:55.485 --> 21:57.146
WAIT, THAT -- THAT'S --
THAT'S WHAT IVY HAS.
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

21:57.146 --> 21:59.439
DR. HUNT, SHE WENT INTO COMPLETE
HEART BLOCK AND LOST HER PULSE.

21:59.439 --> 22:01.150
REMOVE THE OXYGEN MASK
AND AMBU HER.

22:01.150 --> 22:02.902
[ BEEPING CONTINUE ]

22:02.902 --> 22:04.203
PUSH FOR ENOUGH ATROPINE

22:04.203 --> 22:06.155
AND GET A TRANSCUTANEOUS PACER
ON HER NOW.

22:06.155 --> 22:07.867
Woman:
RIGHT AWAY, DOCTOR.

22:15.214 --> 22:17.957
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A. ]

22:17.957 --> 22:20.049
IVY'S TRANSPLANT
WENT VERY WELL.

22:20.049 --> 22:21.511
SHE'S DOING GREAT.

22:21.511 --> 22:22.762
WE'LL MONITOR HER,

22:22.762 --> 22:24.013
AND YOU CAN SEE HER
AS SOON AS SHE WAKES UP.

22:24.013 --> 22:26.516
AND FRANCESCA'S HEART'S
BEEN STABILIZED FOR NOW,

22:26.516 --> 22:30.560
BUT WE ARE GONNA NEED TO IMPLANT
A PACEMAKER AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

22:30.560 --> 22:32.432
AND SHE HAS
CARDIOMYOPATHY?

22:32.432 --> 22:34.434
Cristina: THAT'S WHAT THE TESTS
SHOW, JUST LIKE HER SISTER.

22:34.434 --> 22:36.025
HOW DID BOTH OF THEM
GET THIS?

22:36.025 --> 22:37.607
IT COULD BE
A NUMBER OF THINGS --

22:37.607 --> 22:39.779
UH, VIRAL, GENETIC,
ENVIRONMENTAL.

22:39.779 --> 22:41.861
LIKE, THERE'S SOMETHING
IN OUR HOUSE MAKING THEM SICK?

22:41.861 --> 22:43.282
MOLD OR --
WE CAN'T GO HOME.

22:43.282 --> 22:45.745
IVY JUST GOT A NEW HEART
AND LINK --

22:45.745 --> 22:48.077
Cristina: I SUGGEST WE START
WITH A FAMILY MEDICAL HISTORY

22:48.077 --> 22:49.539
AND WE'LL SEE
IF THERE'S ANY PATTERN

22:49.539 --> 22:50.830
OF HEART DISEASE
IN THE FAMILY,

22:50.830 --> 22:52.752
PARTICULARLY
IN YOUNGER RELATIVES.

22:52.752 --> 22:54.253
HOW SOON CAN WE START?

22:54.253 --> 22:55.755
WHAT ARE THE ODDS,

22:55.755 --> 22:58.878
DEALING WITH TWO
CARDIOMYOPATHIES
ON THE SAME DAY?

22:58.878 --> 23:01.130
I KNOW, AND YOU HAD YOUR
TRIAL PATIENTS TO THINK ABOUT.

23:01.130 --> 23:04.093
BUT ROSS CAN HANDLE THAT.
NO, I'M SAYING,
"WHAT ARE THE ODDS?"

23:04.093 --> 23:06.886
PRESENTING AT THE SAME AGE
IN TWO SISTERS.

23:06.886 --> 23:07.927
IT'S WEIRD, ISN'T IT?

23:07.927 --> 23:09.178
REALLY WEIRD.

23:09.178 --> 23:11.431
TELL YOU WHAT, YOU DO
THE GIRL'S PACEMAKER STAT.

23:11.431 --> 23:12.682
I'LL LOOK
IN TO THE FAMILY HISTORY,

23:12.682 --> 23:14.353
AND WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT.
OKAY.

23:14.353 --> 23:15.975
[ BEEPS ]

23:15.975 --> 23:17.396
98.6.

23:17.396 --> 23:19.398
[ SCOFFS ] I HAVE A COUGH.
FEEL MY GLANDS.

23:19.398 --> 23:20.730
I'M NOT TOUCHING
YOUR GLANDS.

23:20.730 --> 23:22.111
I'VE GOT TO TAKE CARE
OF MY CONDUIT KIDS.

23:22.111 --> 23:24.904
YES! FIRST OF ALL,
SWAP MONKEY!

23:24.904 --> 23:26.075
I HAVE NOT FALLEN,

23:26.075 --> 23:27.617
BUT THOSE ARE HELPLESS CHILDREN
IN THERE,

23:27.617 --> 23:28.868
AND IF I EXPOSE THEM
TO THIS BUG,

23:28.868 --> 23:30.329
IT COULD SET BACK
THE RESEARCH.

23:30.329 --> 23:32.532
DRINK SOME TEA
AND BE A MAN.

23:32.532 --> 23:35.585
I'LL TAKE WEEKEND CALLS
FOR YOU FOR A MONTH.

23:35.585 --> 23:37.166
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

23:37.166 --> 23:39.418
YOU KNOW,
I'D HAVE DONE IT ANYWAY

23:39.418 --> 23:42.842
'CAUSE THOSE ARE JUST
HELPLESS LITTLE CHILDREN.

23:45.635 --> 23:47.136
Alex:
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

23:47.136 --> 23:48.718
MY STUDENT LOANS ARE DEFERRED
TO AFTER MY FELLOWSHIP.

23:48.718 --> 23:50.309
WHICH ENDS REALLY SOON!

23:50.309 --> 23:51.971
ALEX, BASED
ON YOUR CURRENT SALARY,

23:51.971 --> 23:54.814
IT'S GONNA TAKE YOU 20 YEARS
TO PAY OFF THE FULL AMOUNT!

23:54.814 --> 23:56.766
AND THAT'S
WITH A FIXED INTEREST RATE

23:56.766 --> 23:58.608
AND PAYING
TWICE THE MONTHLY MINIMUM.

23:58.608 --> 24:00.229
YOU WAIT ANY LONGER,
IT'LL AMORTIZE! YOU'RE --

24:00.229 --> 24:02.652
ALL RIGHT, BACK OFF,
SCROOGE McDUCK! I'LL BE FINE.

24:02.652 --> 24:05.194
♪ I DON'T KNOW WHEN TO START
OR WHEN TO STOP ♪
YOUR FACE
IS SCROOGE McDUCK!

24:05.194 --> 24:06.946
[ CHUCKLES ]
OHH!

24:06.946 --> 24:08.618
♪ MY LUCK'S LIKE A BUTTON ♪

24:08.618 --> 24:10.660
♪ I CAN'T STOP PUSHING IT ♪
YOUR REJOINDERS
NEED WORK.

24:10.660 --> 24:12.622
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

24:12.622 --> 24:13.833
♪ MY HEAD FEELS LIGHT ♪
YOU KNOW, CAN I JUST --
CAN I JUST TAKE A MINUTE?

24:13.833 --> 24:14.994
I NEED TO COOL DOWN.
OH, NO.

24:14.994 --> 24:16.335
NO, NO, NO.

24:16.335 --> 24:17.877
THAT KIND OF RAGE IS EXACTLY
WHAT WE'RE GONNA NEED.

24:17.877 --> 24:19.999
KEEP IT GOING.
[ SIGHS ]

24:19.999 --> 24:22.131
♪ SEEMS LIKE WITHOUT TENDERNESS
THERE'S SOMETHING MISSING ♪
SCRUB! COME ON. HUSTLE.

24:24.173 --> 24:26.255
HEY. OKAY,
SO WHAT DID YOU THINK?

24:26.255 --> 24:28.467
♪ TENDERNESS, WHERE IS IT? ♪
WELL, THE SURGERY WAS COOL,
BUT, UH, I MEAN,

24:28.467 --> 24:30.720
LEBACKES --
YOU LIKE THAT GUY?

24:30.720 --> 24:32.762
♪ TENDERNESS, WHERE IS IT? ♪
YEAH, HE'S RIDICULOUSLY TALENTED
AND HE RUNS A REALLY FUN O.R.

24:32.762 --> 24:35.555
YEAH, JUST ASK HIM.

24:35.555 --> 24:37.146
♪ I DON'T KNOW WHERE I AM,
BUT I KNOW I DON'T LIKE IT ♪
Lebackes: SURGERY WENT
VERY WELL -- BEAUTIFULLY WELL.

24:37.146 --> 24:38.397
WE'RE LOOKING
AT A FULL RECOVERY,

24:38.397 --> 24:39.979
SO NO NEED
FOR A COLOSTOMY BAG.

24:39.979 --> 24:41.310
REALLY?
YEAH.

24:41.310 --> 24:43.022
HE'S A BIG, STRONG BOY.
HE'S GONNA BE JUST FINE.

24:43.022 --> 24:44.443
MORE THAN JUST FINE.

24:44.443 --> 24:47.156
HE'S GONNA BE PERFECT.
THANK YOU, DR. LEBACKES.

24:47.156 --> 24:49.659
THANK YOU SO MUCH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:49.659 --> 24:52.532
♪ WORDS LIKE CONVICTION
CAN TURN INTO A SENTENCE ♪
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

24:52.532 --> 24:53.953
[ SIGHS ]

24:53.953 --> 24:56.205
THAT'S THE GOOD PART.
THAT'S THE MONEY IN THERE.

24:56.205 --> 24:58.077
IT NEVER GETS OLD.
YEAH.

24:58.077 --> 24:59.709
WELL, LONG DAY,
SUCCESSFUL SURGERY.

24:59.709 --> 25:00.830
YOU KNOW
WHAT TIME IT IS NOW?

25:00.830 --> 25:03.122
TIME FOR MORE SURGERIES?
TIME TO UNWIND.

25:03.122 --> 25:05.625
KAREV,
DO YOU PLAY GOLF?

25:05.625 --> 25:07.046
♪ JUST HALF A CHANCE ♪

25:07.046 --> 25:10.509
♪ MAKE SURE THAT ONE NIGHT
YOU'RE HERE ♪

25:10.509 --> 25:12.932
♪ BUT NEXT NIGHT YOU'RE NOT ♪
OH, DEAR LORD IN HEAVEN,
NO! YOU'RE NOT --

25:12.932 --> 25:14.183
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!

25:14.183 --> 25:15.595
WHAT?
DR. SHEPHERD,
DON'T COME IN HERE!

25:15.595 --> 25:17.977
BUT YOU -- YOU PAGED ME.
THIS CHILD HAS S.C.I.D.

25:17.977 --> 25:20.229
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
IF YOU'RE SICK AT ALL,
YOU CANNOT BE IN HERE.

25:20.229 --> 25:22.021
CLOSE THAT DOOR.
OH, MY GOD.

25:22.021 --> 25:23.853
♪ TENDERNESS, WHERE IS IT? ♪
WELL, SEE,
I'M THE ONLY ONE AVAILABLE.

25:23.853 --> 25:25.565
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
YOU GOT A BETTER IDEA?

25:25.565 --> 25:27.777
YEAH.
YEAH, I THINK I DO.

25:27.777 --> 25:28.738
WHAT?

25:28.738 --> 25:30.409
Richard:
OKAY, BABCOCK, PLEASE.

25:30.409 --> 25:31.410
HERE YOU GO, DOCTOR.

25:31.410 --> 25:33.703
AND UMBILICAL TAPE.

25:33.703 --> 25:36.115
THIS IS A HUGE ABSCESS.

25:36.115 --> 25:37.867
WE SHOULD HANG
ANOTHER UNIT OF BLOOD.

25:37.867 --> 25:39.789
ANOTHER LITER
OF SALINE, PLEASE.

25:39.789 --> 25:41.040
♪ I HELD YOUR HANDS ♪
MURPHY, HE'S ALREADY
GOT A UNIT OF L.R. HANGING.

25:41.040 --> 25:42.001
♪ RINGS BUT NONE
ON THAT FINGER ♪
KEEP UP.

25:42.001 --> 25:43.122
IT'S NOT FOR HIM.

25:43.122 --> 25:44.373
♪ WE DANCED AND DANCED ♪
IT'S FOR ME.

25:44.373 --> 25:45.795
♪ I WAS SCARED TO GO MUCH
FURTHER WITH IT ♪

25:45.795 --> 25:48.127
MURPHY,
ARE YOU ON AN I.V.?

25:48.127 --> 25:49.298
♪ JUST HALF A CHANCE ♪
I'M SORRY. IT'S JUST THAT
I'M SUPER DEHYDRATED.

25:49.298 --> 25:51.550
AND I CAN'T KEEP
ANYTHING DOWN.

25:51.550 --> 25:53.262
♪ MAKE SURE THAT ONE NIGHT
YOU'RE HERE ♪
IT'S REALLY HELPING
WITH THE DIZZINESS, TOO.

25:53.262 --> 25:54.513
MAYBE
YOU SHOULD GO HOME.

25:54.513 --> 25:56.726
YEAH, MURPHY,
MAYBE YOU SH--
NO!

25:56.726 --> 25:58.137
♪ IT ALWAYS LEAVES ME
SEARCHING FOR A LITTLE ♪
NO, I HAVE FOUND A WAY
TO PUSH THROUGH,

25:58.137 --> 25:59.769
AND I'M NOT GONNA BREAK
THE UNSPOKEN RULE

25:59.769 --> 26:01.100
EVERYONE
KEEPS SPEAKING ABOUT.

26:01.100 --> 26:03.062
IT'S LIKE YOU SAY, SIR --
UNLESS MY PRESENCE HERE...

26:03.062 --> 26:05.274
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
...IS DOING MY PATIENT MORE HARM
THAN MY ABSENCE WOULD,

26:05.274 --> 26:06.896
IT'S MY DUTY TO STAY.

26:06.896 --> 26:08.277
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
IMPRESSIVE, MURPHY.

26:08.277 --> 26:09.739
I'M PROUD OF YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:09.739 --> 26:11.360
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
YAY ME.

26:11.360 --> 26:13.032
♪ TENDERNESS ♪

26:13.032 --> 26:15.695
YOU LOOK REALLY COOL.

26:15.695 --> 26:17.957
YOU DON'T LOOK RIDICULOUS
AT ALL. HOW DO YOU FEEL?

26:17.957 --> 26:19.118
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
I'M FINE.

26:19.118 --> 26:20.329
LET'S KEEP WORKING.

26:20.329 --> 26:21.791
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
ROGER, MAJOR TOM.

26:21.791 --> 26:23.753
COMMENCING COUNTDOWN.

26:23.753 --> 26:25.414
♪ TENDERNESS ♪

26:25.414 --> 26:28.628
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
OKAY, I'M GONNA...
TAKE THIS SLOW.

26:28.628 --> 26:30.880
♪ TENDERNESS ♪

26:30.880 --> 26:32.632
♪ TENDERNESS ♪
[ BUZZING ]

26:32.632 --> 26:34.764
Callie: ALL RIGHT.

26:34.764 --> 26:36.135
OKAY.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

26:36.135 --> 26:38.768
[ SIGHS ]

26:38.768 --> 26:40.219
REALLY?
REALLY.

26:40.219 --> 26:42.221
[ LAUGHS ]
ALL RIGHT, HERE.

26:42.221 --> 26:44.273
HOLD THAT THERE. THAT.

26:44.273 --> 26:47.777
NOW, YOU
GOT TO HIT IT HARD.

26:49.819 --> 26:52.441
THIS JUST -- IT --
THIS FEELS WRONG.

26:52.441 --> 26:54.283
NO, HEY, LOOK, I TOLD YOU
THE BONE IS MISALIGNED,

26:54.283 --> 26:55.995
ALL RIGHT, SO WE
HAVE TO COMPLETE THE BREAK

26:55.995 --> 26:57.576
BEFORE WE CAN
PUT IT BACK TOGETHER.

26:57.576 --> 26:59.448
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

26:59.448 --> 27:02.662
[ LAUGHS ] OH, MY GOD.
DON'T BE A WEENIE.

27:02.662 --> 27:03.793
I CAN'T!

27:03.793 --> 27:05.204
LOOK, YOU'RE STRONGER
THAN YOU THINK.

27:05.204 --> 27:06.746
NOW JUST --
NO, I'M STRONGER
THAN YOU THINK.

27:06.746 --> 27:08.918
I'VE PUT GUYS
IN THE HOSPITAL BEFORE.

27:08.918 --> 27:10.920
OKAY, YEAH, I KNOW.
THE GUY FROM O.B.

27:10.920 --> 27:13.052
AND TWO GUYS
BEFORE HIM.

27:13.052 --> 27:14.844
WOW. OKAY. WOW.

27:14.844 --> 27:16.886
LOOK, WHEN I GET MAD,
I GET...

27:16.886 --> 27:19.598
[ SIGHS ]
I DON'T TRUST MYSELF.

27:19.598 --> 27:20.970
THAT'S WHY I THOUGHT
I HURT HIM THIS MORNING.

27:20.970 --> 27:23.022
I DON'T WANT TO DO THIS.
I DON'T WANT TO HURT PEOPLE.

27:23.022 --> 27:24.103
I WANT TO FIX THEM.

27:24.103 --> 27:25.434
WELL, THIS IS THE ONLY WAY
TO FIX HIM.

27:25.434 --> 27:26.856
AND IT'S AN EASY FIX.

27:26.856 --> 27:28.527
LOOK, THAT'S THE NICE THING
ABOUT ORTHO.

27:28.527 --> 27:30.109
MOST OF THEM
ARE EASY FIXES,

27:30.109 --> 27:34.113
BUT THEY TAKE STRENGTH AND POWER
THAT NOT A LOT OF PEOPLE HAVE...

27:34.113 --> 27:35.985
OR THE FEARLESSNESS.
AAH!

27:35.985 --> 27:37.987
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

27:37.987 --> 27:39.448
OHH.

27:39.448 --> 27:40.990
WHAT'S NEXT?
UH, NEXT.

27:40.990 --> 27:44.704
NEXT...WE DRILL.

27:44.704 --> 27:46.045
[ DRILL WHIRS ]
YES.

27:46.045 --> 27:47.496
[ LAUGHS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:53.422 --> 27:54.463
April: HOW YOU DOING,
DR. SHEPHERD?

27:54.463 --> 27:56.295
I'M GOOD.

27:56.295 --> 27:59.759
JUST...TAKING IT SLOW.

27:59.759 --> 28:02.972
ALMOST...
IMPERCEPTIBLY SLOW.

28:02.972 --> 28:06.265
AT THIS RATE, YOU'RE NOT EVEN
GONNA MAKE YOUR BIG CONFERENCE.

28:06.265 --> 28:07.516
OKAY, KEPNER,
STEP IN HERE.

28:09.108 --> 28:11.230
DENUDE THE SINUS OF MUCOSA.

28:11.230 --> 28:14.403
AS A TRAUMA SURGEON,
YOU NEED TO LEARN THIS.

28:14.403 --> 28:16.695
ESPECIALLY SINCE HE'S ABOUT
TO RALPH IN HIS SPACE SUIT.

28:16.695 --> 28:18.197
BAILEY, SHUT UP.
[ LAUGHS ]

28:18.197 --> 28:22.281
OKAY, KEPNER, TAKE
THE...PERIOSTEAL ELEVATOR.

28:22.281 --> 28:24.163
YES, SIR.

28:24.163 --> 28:27.747
[ SIGHS ]

28:27.747 --> 28:29.538
[ GOLF BALL CRACKS ]

28:29.538 --> 28:31.170
Announcer: IT'S A LONG DRIVE.

28:31.170 --> 28:33.172
OHH, COME ON!
OHH!

28:33.172 --> 28:35.925
I'M TELLING YOU, YOU GOT
TOO MUCH TURN IN YOUR BACKSWING.

28:35.925 --> 28:37.216
HERE. WATCH THIS.

28:37.216 --> 28:39.218
[ GOLF BALL CRACKS ]

28:39.218 --> 28:42.301
OLIVER HITS THE BALL
FROM THE TEE AND...

28:42.301 --> 28:44.513
IT'S A HOLE IN ONE!
NICE.

28:44.513 --> 28:46.105
ALL OF THIS.

28:46.105 --> 28:47.606
AND YOUR CLINIC IS NICER
THAN MY HOUSE.

28:47.606 --> 28:49.188
YEAH. MINE, TOO.

28:49.188 --> 28:50.940
ACTUALLY, I'M KIDDING.

28:50.940 --> 28:52.061
MY HOUSE IS WAY BETTER.

28:52.061 --> 28:53.612
OHH!
[ CROWD GROANS ]

28:53.612 --> 28:55.734
AND YOU DON'T HAVE ANY MORE
PATIENTS OR, UH, ANYTHING TODAY?

28:55.734 --> 28:57.356
NAH. I LIKE
TO SPACE THINGS OUT.

28:57.356 --> 28:59.568
KEEP THINGS CIVILIZED.

28:59.568 --> 29:01.660
IT'S ONE OF THE PERKS
OF HAVING YOUR OWN PRACTICE.

29:01.660 --> 29:03.322
OHH!
SWINGS, AND IN THE BUNKER.

29:03.322 --> 29:05.164
[ CROWD GROANS ]
I'M IN THE BUNKER.
YOU'RE UP.

29:06.455 --> 29:08.327
[ GOLF BALL CRACKS ]

29:08.327 --> 29:10.960
MY PARTNERS AND I ARE TALKING
ABOUT EXPANDING OUR PRACTICE,

29:10.960 --> 29:13.042
BRINGING IN SOMEONE NEW.
ANOTHER TOUGH SHOT
FOR ALEX.

29:13.042 --> 29:14.253
WHERE ARE YOU
AT WITH YOUR FELLOWSHIP?

29:14.253 --> 29:16.175
WHAT? MY WHAT?

29:16.175 --> 29:17.837
HAVE YOU STARTED THINKING
ABOUT WHAT'S NEXT?

29:19.298 --> 29:20.800
WELL,
I-I-I LIKE WHERE I AM.

29:20.800 --> 29:22.972
SURE. OF COURSE.

29:22.972 --> 29:24.884
ROBBINS IS GREAT.

29:24.884 --> 29:28.097
BUT...THE PERKS HERE...

29:28.097 --> 29:29.849
[ GOLF BALL CRACKS ]
OLIVER SWINGS.

29:29.849 --> 29:31.851
...ARE MORE THAN JUST BIG TVs
AND FANCY OFFICES.

29:31.851 --> 29:33.062
NICE SHOT OUT OF THE BUNKER.
OLIVER WINS.

29:33.062 --> 29:34.773
MAKING MORE MONEY
MEANS BEING ABLE TO DONATE

29:34.773 --> 29:36.155
MORE MONEY
TO DO MORE OUTREACH.

29:36.155 --> 29:39.198
I, UH, STARTED AN AFRICAN
EXCHANGE PROGRAM AT GSM.

29:39.198 --> 29:40.569
RIGHT. LIKE THAT.

29:40.569 --> 29:41.610
I SET MY OWN HOURS.

29:41.610 --> 29:43.452
SO I'M TAKING
A MONTH OFF NEXT SPRING

29:43.452 --> 29:46.245
SO I CAN GO TO MAFRAQ
AND TREAT SYRIAN REFUGEES.

29:46.245 --> 29:49.328
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
GIVE IT SOME THOUGHT.
I THINK YOU'D BE A GOOD FIT.

29:49.328 --> 29:52.501
IT'S A 250K BUY-IN, WHICH YOU'LL
PAY OFF IN TWO YEARS, TOPS.

29:52.501 --> 29:54.413
ANOTHER TWO,
AND I GUARANTEE YOU'LL PAY OFF

29:54.413 --> 29:56.295
ALL YOUR STUDENT LOANS
WITH CASH TO SPARE.

29:56.295 --> 29:59.128
PLUS, YOU, TOO, COULD HAVE
YOUR NAME EMBLAZONED

29:59.128 --> 30:02.091
ON A FINE WRITING UTENSIL
JUST LIKE THIS.

30:09.138 --> 30:12.101
[ SUCTION SLURPING ]
MURPHY, CAN YOU SUCTION OUT
SOME OF THAT FECAL DEBRIS?

30:12.101 --> 30:13.893
AND WHILE YOU'RE AT IT,
THIS ABSCESS

30:13.893 --> 30:15.895
IS GOING INTO
THE RETROPERITONEAL CAVITY.

30:15.895 --> 30:17.276
CAN YOU SUCTION
SOME OF THAT PUSS

30:17.276 --> 30:19.318
AROUND
THAT NECROTIC TISSUE.

30:19.318 --> 30:21.320
[ SLURPING CONTINUES ]
FEELS GOOD,
DOESN'T IT, MURPHY?

30:21.320 --> 30:24.113
YOU KNOW, I REMEMBER
WORKING A 24-HOUR SHIFT

30:24.113 --> 30:25.945
THROUGH A BOUT OF SALMONELLA
IN MY THIRD YEAR.

30:25.945 --> 30:27.156
Meredith:
SUCTION, PLEASE.

30:27.156 --> 30:29.158
[ SUCTION SLURPING ]
PORK WAS THE CULPRIT.

30:29.158 --> 30:30.619
BAD PORK.

30:30.619 --> 30:34.833
IT TASTED FINE, BUT I REMEMBER
IT BEING A LITTLE...SLICK.

30:34.833 --> 30:38.217
BUT A PHYSICIAN
DOESN'T SUCCUMB TO ILLNESS.

30:38.217 --> 30:41.090
SHE CONQUERS IT, RIGHT?

30:41.090 --> 30:43.222
[ SLURPING CONTINUES ]

30:43.222 --> 30:45.554
RIGHT, MURPHY?
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

30:45.554 --> 30:47.887
ARE YOU NOT ANSWERING BECAUSE
YOU'VE THROWN UP IN YOUR MOUTH?

30:47.887 --> 30:50.639
MM-HMM.
BACK AWAY
FROM THE FIELD, MURPHY.

30:50.639 --> 30:51.931
YEAH, GO HOME.

30:51.931 --> 30:53.142
GOOD EFFORT, MURPHY.

30:58.857 --> 30:59.939
LIGHTWEIGHT.

30:59.939 --> 31:01.320
WHAT A WUSS.

31:01.320 --> 31:03.322
Owen:
HEY, HOW'S IT GOING?

31:03.322 --> 31:04.573
Cristina: WE'RE ADVANCING
THE LEADS NOW.

31:04.573 --> 31:06.325
SO I WENT THROUGH
THE McNEILS' FAMILY HISTORY.

31:06.325 --> 31:08.988
NOTHING SPECIFICALLY INDICATES
THAT IT'S GENETIC.

31:08.988 --> 31:11.290
SOMETHING IS DAMAGING
THESE KIDS' HEARTS.

31:11.290 --> 31:13.202
HERS IS ENLARGED,
AND HER E.F. IS LOW.

31:13.202 --> 31:14.753
SHE'S GONNA WIND UP
ON THE TRANSPLANT LIST.

31:14.753 --> 31:15.955
WELL, IT'S STILL EARLY
FOR THAT.

31:15.955 --> 31:17.626
THE McNEILS
HAVE GIVEN YOU CONSENT

31:17.626 --> 31:20.499
TO DO A BIOPSY
WHILE YOU'RE STILL IN THERE.
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

31:20.499 --> 31:22.171
OH, AND MURPHY APPARENTLY
JUST THREW UP IN AN O.R.,

31:22.171 --> 31:25.174
SO I NEED TO START RESCHEDULING
ELECTIVE PROCEDURES.

31:25.174 --> 31:27.176
OH, IT'S GOT TO BE VIRAL.
CLEARLY.

31:27.176 --> 31:29.008
SHE'S THE EIGHTH SURGEON I'VE
HAD COME DOWN WITH THIS THING.

31:29.008 --> 31:30.389
NO. THIS -- THE McNEILS.

31:30.389 --> 31:32.721
IT'S GOT TO BE
VIRAL MYOCARDITIS.

31:32.721 --> 31:35.314
I BET YOU IT IS.
BRING ON THE PACING.

31:35.314 --> 31:38.067
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

31:38.067 --> 31:40.279
Stephanie: ALL RIGHT,
WE ARE ALMOST DONE.

31:40.279 --> 31:42.321
YES. SO DON'T PEE.

31:42.321 --> 31:44.283
Adam: EXCUSE ME.
DON'T YOU PEE ON ME.

31:44.283 --> 31:46.025
DR. EDWARDS.

31:46.025 --> 31:47.196
DR. MURPHY WENT HOME SICK

31:47.196 --> 31:48.287
IN THE MIDDLE
OF AN INTESTINAL RESECTION.

31:48.287 --> 31:50.659
ARE YOU AVAILABLE?
OH, ABSOLUTELY.

31:50.659 --> 31:52.491
DO YOU THINK YOU CAN
TAKE OVER THESE PATIENTS?
NO.

31:52.491 --> 31:53.832
[ LIQUID SPLASHING ]

31:53.832 --> 31:55.334
OH, HEY! COME --
OH, ALL RIGHT.

31:55.334 --> 31:57.206
HEY, OKAY, WE HAD A DEAL.

31:58.037 --> 31:59.959
[ SIGHS ]
I'LL TELL THEM YOU'RE BUSY.

31:59.959 --> 32:01.590
NO, NO, NO. NO, NO.
I'M NOT BUSY.

32:01.590 --> 32:04.003
I'M NOT...
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

32:08.807 --> 32:10.139
Callie:
WE USED PLATES AND SCREWS

32:10.139 --> 32:12.141
SO THAT THE BONE
WILL HEAL STRAIGHT.

32:12.141 --> 32:15.264
SO HIS BODY --
HIS ORGANICALLY PURE,

32:15.264 --> 32:17.606
GRASS-FED BODY
IS FULL OF TITANIUM?

32:17.606 --> 32:19.688
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:19.688 --> 32:21.440
[ Laughing ]
CAN I GET A LIST

32:21.440 --> 32:24.023
OF THE MATERIALS
THAT YOU GUYS USED?

32:24.023 --> 32:25.944
THE -- THE RODS?

32:25.944 --> 32:29.698
I DON'T KNOW, LIKE, ANAESTHESIA
AND STUFF FOR -- FOR HIM?

32:29.698 --> 32:30.909
UH, WELL, I DON'T KNOW.

32:30.909 --> 32:32.161
UM, THAT COULD
TAKE A WHILE.

32:32.161 --> 32:33.872
I'D HAVE TO CONTACT
DISTRIBUTORS.

32:33.872 --> 32:35.074
NORMALLY,
I WOULDN'T ASK THIS,

32:35.074 --> 32:37.076
BUT OUR DAD DIED
WHEN WE WERE REALLY YOUNG,

32:37.076 --> 32:40.339
AND HE WAS DONE IN BY
CORNED-BEEF HASH AND CIGARETTES.

32:40.339 --> 32:41.710
AND SINCE THEN,
LOGAN'S BEEN

32:41.710 --> 32:43.342
OBSESSED WITH WHAT HE PUTS
IN HIS BODY.

32:43.342 --> 32:44.423
HE'S A PAIN IN THE ASS.

32:44.423 --> 32:45.754
I WISH HE WOULDN'T TAKE IT
SO FAR,

32:45.754 --> 32:48.757
BUT...THAT'S JUST
HOW HE DEALS.

32:48.757 --> 32:50.179
I'LL DO IT.

32:50.179 --> 32:52.261
REALLY?

32:52.261 --> 32:53.352
SURE. NO BIGGIE.

32:54.853 --> 32:56.595
ANY CHANCE THE TITANIUM
WAS LOCALLY MINED?

32:56.595 --> 32:58.517
UH...
UH...

32:58.517 --> 33:00.559
[ LAUGHS ]

33:00.559 --> 33:04.153
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

33:04.153 --> 33:06.775
OHH, YOU'RE FEELING IT,
AREN'T YOU?

33:06.775 --> 33:08.157
THE ORTHO GLOW.
THANK YOU.

33:08.157 --> 33:10.159
OHH,
IS THAT WHAT THIS IS?

33:10.159 --> 33:11.320
MM-HMM.
MM!

33:11.320 --> 33:13.202
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

33:13.202 --> 33:16.415
OHH, YOU KNOW, I CAN BE
FAIRLY TURBULENT MYSELF.

33:16.415 --> 33:21.250
YEAH, I'VE HAD MY SHARE
OF THINGS TO GET ANGRY ABOUT.

33:21.250 --> 33:23.832
ORTHO'S SAVED ME
A COUPLE OF TIMES.

33:23.832 --> 33:26.255
I GET TO WORK MY CRAP OUT
AND SOMEONE ELSE

33:26.255 --> 33:28.337
IS HEALED IN THE PROCESS
AND I GET PAID.

33:28.337 --> 33:30.129
IT'S A WIN-WIN-WIN.

33:30.129 --> 33:34.803
RIGHT NOW I FEEL LIKE I MIGHT
NEVER GET ANGRY AGAIN.

33:34.803 --> 33:37.726
[ Chuckling ] OH, SWEETIE.
YOU DATE ALEX KAREV.

33:37.726 --> 33:39.268
YOU ALWAYS HAVE A REASON
TO BE ANGRY.

33:39.268 --> 33:40.269
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

33:40.269 --> 33:42.441
[ PEOPLE COUGHING ]

33:42.441 --> 33:44.483
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

33:48.107 --> 33:49.358
HEY,
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

33:49.358 --> 33:51.110
YOU'VE GOT FIVE KIDS
TO DISCHARGE.

33:51.110 --> 33:52.951
THIS PLACE
IS DISGUSTING.

33:52.951 --> 33:54.653
AREN'T YOU SUPPOSED TO BE,
UH, SICK BY NOW?

33:54.653 --> 33:56.455
OH, CRAP.
I'M LOSING MY TOUCH.

33:56.455 --> 33:58.157
IT WAS MY SUPERPOWER.
AND NOW I'VE LOST IT.

33:58.157 --> 33:59.618
HOW MUCH MONEY
DO YOU MAKE?
EXCUSE ME?

33:59.618 --> 34:01.210
I MEAN, AS AN ATTENDING HERE.
WHAT'S YOUR SALARY?

34:01.210 --> 34:03.122
I'M NOT ANSWERING THAT.
WHY,
BECAUSE YOU'RE ASHAMED?

34:03.122 --> 34:04.543
NO,
BECAUSE IT'S CLASSLESS!

34:04.543 --> 34:06.215
AND YOU SHOULD BE ASHAMED,
YOU HOBO.

34:06.215 --> 34:08.627
LOOK, JUST TELL ME.
NO, GET TO WORK, ALEX.

34:08.627 --> 34:10.629
[ COUGHING CONTINUES ]
[ SIREN WAILING ]

34:15.013 --> 34:17.386
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

34:20.349 --> 34:23.182
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

34:23.182 --> 34:25.984
OH, GOD.

34:25.984 --> 34:27.356
OKAY.

34:27.356 --> 34:28.777
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

34:28.777 --> 34:30.609
IF I CAN DO SURGERY,
I CAN STAND AND TALK TO PEOPLE.

34:30.609 --> 34:32.491
I HAVE TO.
IT'S NOT WORTH IT.

34:32.491 --> 34:33.742
SEE, YOU'VE NEVER
REALLY BEEN

34:33.742 --> 34:35.114
ON BOARD
WITH THIS WHOLE PROJECT.

34:35.114 --> 34:36.905
NO, DEREK, AT SOME POINT,
YOU HAVE TO ASK YOURSELF

34:36.905 --> 34:39.618
IS YOUR PRESENCE HERE GOING
TO DO MORE HARM THAN GOOD?

34:39.618 --> 34:40.789
[ GROANS ]
TRUST ME.

34:40.789 --> 34:42.161
YOU'RE BETTER OFF
CALLING THIS THING OFF

34:42.161 --> 34:45.254
THAN TO GET UP ON THAT STAGE
AND VOMIT...OR WORSE.

34:45.254 --> 34:47.336
MEREDITH, I HAVE NO CHOICE.
THIS IS WHAT WE DO.

34:47.336 --> 34:49.418
WE PUSH THROUGH.

34:52.211 --> 34:54.213
WHOA.

34:58.807 --> 35:00.809
[ PANTING ]

35:04.353 --> 35:06.685
OKAY?

35:11.780 --> 35:14.072
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]
[ SIGHS ]

35:14.072 --> 35:15.904
OH, NO.

35:15.904 --> 35:17.115
OH, NO, NO.

35:17.115 --> 35:18.577
Kathleen:
DR. SHEPHERD, DON'T GET UP.

35:18.577 --> 35:20.949
YOU'RE DEHYDRATED.
YOU HAVE I.V. PHENERGAN.

35:20.949 --> 35:24.373
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO PULL OUT YOUR I.V.

35:24.373 --> 35:27.916
I'M...

35:27.916 --> 35:30.589
HERE YOU GO,
DR. SHEPHERD.

35:30.589 --> 35:32.171
OHH.
HERE YOU GO.

35:32.171 --> 35:34.092
[ GRUNTS ]

35:34.092 --> 35:36.175
[ SIREN WAILING ]

35:42.140 --> 35:43.762
YOU'RE NOT EVEN WARM!

35:43.762 --> 35:45.184
[ SIGHS ]
I DO FEEL MUCH BETTER.

35:45.184 --> 35:47.065
I HAVE BEEN
CHANGING DIAPERS,

35:47.065 --> 35:48.817
RESTARTING I.V.s,
GETTING PEED ON.

35:48.817 --> 35:50.769
I MISSED OUT ON A SURGERY
'CAUSE YOU'RE UP HERE

35:50.769 --> 35:52.321
SLEEPING OFF
YOUR IMAGINARY ILLNESS.

35:52.321 --> 35:53.982
ARE THE KIDS OKAY?
DID ANY OF THEM GET SICK?

35:53.982 --> 35:56.074
NO. THEY'RE FINE.

35:56.074 --> 35:57.736
YOU WON'T BE.

35:57.736 --> 35:59.538
OHH,
THANK YOU, STEPHANIE.

35:59.538 --> 36:01.119
SERIOUSLY.

36:01.119 --> 36:02.160
YOU'RE WELCOME.

36:02.160 --> 36:04.082
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]
ROSS.

36:04.082 --> 36:05.664
HOW ARE
THE CONDUIT PATIENTS?

36:05.664 --> 36:06.995
UH, THEY'RE GREAT.

36:06.995 --> 36:08.377
GREAT NUMBERS,
NO PROBLEMS.

36:08.377 --> 36:09.918
PERFECT DAY 30.
GOOD.

36:09.918 --> 36:11.500
WELL, I'LL SEE YOU UPSTAIRS.
WE'LL GET STARTED ON THE REPORT.

36:13.212 --> 36:15.133
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
SO YOU'RE JU--

36:15.133 --> 36:16.255
ALL YOUR WEEKEND CALLS,

36:16.255 --> 36:17.796
AND I'M YOUR SWAP MONKEY
FOR TWO MONTHS.

36:21.390 --> 36:23.011
IT'S JUST EXCITING.

36:23.011 --> 36:25.304
YOU KNOW, YOU MEET SOMEONE
AND THERE'S JUST...

36:25.304 --> 36:27.185
A CONNECTION.

36:27.185 --> 36:29.187
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]
OH, WE JUST CLICKED.

36:29.187 --> 36:31.149
SHE'S JUST --
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

36:31.149 --> 36:33.312
SHE JUST -- SHE GETS IT.
SHE GETS ME.

36:33.312 --> 36:35.404
AND THERE'S STILL EVERY CHANCE
THAT IT MIGHT NOT WORK OUT.

36:35.404 --> 36:39.448
I MEAN, ONLY SOMETHING LIKE 4%
OF ORTHO SURGEONS ARE WOMEN.

36:39.448 --> 36:43.702
[ SIGHS ] BUT THAT'S ALSO WHY
IT WOULD BE SO COOL.

36:43.702 --> 36:45.284
Arizona: CALLIE.
YEAH?

36:50.829 --> 36:52.000
OH! MY GOD.
DID YOU FALL?

36:52.000 --> 36:53.752
NO, NO, NO.

36:53.752 --> 36:56.675
THE FLOOR IS JUST
REALLY NICE AND COOL.

36:56.675 --> 36:59.007
AND THIS IS MY FRIEND.

36:59.007 --> 37:01.049
BUT GUESS WHAT.
WHAT?

37:01.049 --> 37:02.140
I'VE STILL GOT IT.

37:02.140 --> 37:04.553
MY SUPERPOWERS
ARE INTACT.

37:04.553 --> 37:06.345
YEAH.
YAY.

37:06.345 --> 37:09.187
SUPER.

37:12.691 --> 37:13.692
[ MONITOR BEEPS ]

37:19.027 --> 37:20.859
David: [ Distorted ] HOW LONG
WILL HE HAVE TO BE LIKE THIS?

37:20.859 --> 37:22.951
Miranda: [ Distorted ]
WELL, AT LEAST UNTIL THE
IMMEDIATE INFECTION IS OVER.

37:22.951 --> 37:25.784
AFTER THAT
IS HARD TO SAY.
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

37:25.784 --> 37:28.917
Teresa: [ Distorted ] HOW IS HE
GONNA HEAL IF HE'S STRESSED OUT,

37:28.917 --> 37:30.168
IF HE CAN'T
EVEN BE COMFORTABLE?

37:30.168 --> 37:31.960
WE'LL HAVE TO TRUST
THAT THE MULTITUDE

37:31.960 --> 37:33.962
OF ANTIBIOTICS
WILL DO THEIR JOBS.

37:33.962 --> 37:36.044
April: [ Distorted ] IF HIS
IMMUNITY DOESN'T COME BACK UP,

37:36.044 --> 37:37.586
IT'S VERY POSSIBLE
THAT HE'LL NEED TO BE

37:37.586 --> 37:39.928
IN SOME SORT OF ISOLATION
FOR THE REST OF HIS LIFE.

37:39.928 --> 37:41.009
THE REST OF HIS LIFE?

37:41.009 --> 37:43.342
BABY!

37:43.342 --> 37:44.723
MOM! DAD!

37:44.723 --> 37:45.974
David:
HEY. WE LOVE YOU, CHAMP!

37:45.974 --> 37:47.476
[ Crying ] WE'RE RIGHT HERE
FOR YOU, BUDDY.

37:47.476 --> 37:49.227
DON'T BE SCARED.
WE'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

37:49.227 --> 37:50.479
WE'RE RIGHT HERE.

37:50.479 --> 37:51.890
MOM.
WE'RE RIGHT HERE, BRADEN.

37:51.890 --> 37:53.021
CHAMP, IT'S OKAY.
DON'T WORRY.

37:53.021 --> 37:54.983
WE'RE NEVER GONNA
LEAVE YOU. OKAY?

37:54.983 --> 37:56.234
WE LOVE YOU.

37:57.025 --> 37:59.608
♪ CLOCK STRIKES UPON THE HOUR ♪

37:59.608 --> 38:02.070
Meredith:
IT'S A KNOWN FACT

38:02.070 --> 38:04.663
THAT DOCTORS MAKE
THE WORST PATIENTS.

38:04.663 --> 38:06.665
♪ AND THE SUN BEGINS TO FADE ♪
[ SIREN WAILING ]

38:06.665 --> 38:07.996
HEY.

38:07.996 --> 38:11.410
YOU OKAY?

38:11.410 --> 38:15.043
♪ STILL ENOUGH TIME
TO FIGURE OUT ♪
I BROUGHT YOU SOME HOT SOUP.

38:17.626 --> 38:19.087
[ JACKSON GRUNTS ]

38:19.087 --> 38:21.380
♪ HOW TO CHASE MY BLUES AWAY ♪

38:21.380 --> 38:22.551
HELLO?

38:22.551 --> 38:24.343
GET OUT. OH.

38:24.343 --> 38:25.884
OKAY, ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

38:25.884 --> 38:28.347
♪ I'VE DONE ALL RIGHT
UP TILL NOW ♪

38:28.347 --> 38:31.099
[ VOMITS ]

38:31.099 --> 38:36.234
♪ IT'S THE LIGHT OF DAY
THAT SHOWS ME HOW ♪

38:36.234 --> 38:37.936
[ SIGHS ]

38:40.068 --> 38:43.942
♪ WHEN THE NIGHT FALLS ♪

38:43.942 --> 38:46.114
♪ LONELINESS CALLS ♪

38:46.114 --> 38:48.326
YEAH.
[ GRUNTS, GROANS ]

38:48.326 --> 38:50.158
I'M HERE
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING, OKAY?

38:50.158 --> 38:52.160
[ GROANS ]

38:52.160 --> 38:53.912
[ RETCHES ]

38:53.912 --> 38:55.043
OKAY.

38:55.043 --> 39:00.959
♪ OH, I WANNA DANCE
WITH SOMEBODY ♪

39:00.959 --> 39:03.171
WE IGNORE OUR SYMPTOMS

39:03.171 --> 39:05.724
♪ I WANNA FEEL THE HEAT
WITH SOMEBODY ♪
...UNTIL WE'RE FACEDOWN
ON THE GROUND.

39:05.724 --> 39:08.016
YOU KNOW, I ACTUALLY DUG MY CRAP
OUT OF THE TRASH.

39:08.016 --> 39:10.929
♪ YEAH, I WANNA DANCE
WITH SOMEBODY ♪
THERE'S LIKE 85 JOKES
I COULD MAKE RIGHT NOW.

39:10.929 --> 39:13.732
GO AHEAD, CHUCKLES.
MAKE YOUR JOKES.

39:13.732 --> 39:15.814
BUT SIT DOWN AND PAY YOUR BILLS
WHILE YOU GIGGLE.

39:15.814 --> 39:17.936
WHY DO YOU EVEN CARE?

39:17.936 --> 39:19.357
♪ WITH SOMEBODY WHO LOVES ME ♪
I KNOW THAT YOU WOULD RATHER
JUST SHOVE STUFF ASIDE,

39:19.357 --> 39:20.939
OUT OF SIGHT, OUT OF MIND,

39:20.939 --> 39:22.941
BUT THE LONGER YOU WAIT,
THE WORSE YOU MAKE IT.

39:22.941 --> 39:24.483
LOOK AT YOUR DAD.

39:24.483 --> 39:26.154
YOU AVOIDED HIM
FOR YEARS,

39:26.154 --> 39:28.036
AND WHEN YOU FINALLY
HAD TO DEAL WITH HIM,

39:28.036 --> 39:29.197
IT WAS TORTURE.

39:29.197 --> 39:30.328
BUT YOU DEALT WITH HIM.

39:30.328 --> 39:31.910
AND THERE'S NO WAY
YOU CAN TELL ME

39:31.910 --> 39:33.251
THAT YOU DON'T
FEEL BETTER.

39:33.251 --> 39:34.873
IT'S THAT EASY, HUH?
YEAH.

39:34.873 --> 39:36.254
IT'S AN EASY FIX.

39:36.254 --> 39:39.087
AND EASY FIXES
ARE JUST SO SATISFYING.

39:39.087 --> 39:41.049
♪ SPINNING THROUGH THE TOWN ♪

39:44.503 --> 39:47.095
♪ SOONER OR LATER
THE FEVER ENDS ♪

39:47.095 --> 39:49.097
[ DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE ]

39:49.097 --> 39:51.009
I MAY HAVE FIGURED OUT
AN EASIER ONE.

39:51.009 --> 39:53.602
♪ AND I WIND UP FEELING DOWN ♪

39:53.602 --> 39:55.604
[ HUMMING GEORGE CLINTON'S
"ATOMIC DOG" ]

39:58.066 --> 39:59.688
♪ I NEED A WOMAN
WHO'LL TAKE A CHANCE ♪

39:59.688 --> 40:01.399
WE LIKE TO THINK

40:01.399 --> 40:03.692
WE'RE A DIFFERENT SPECIES
THAN OUR PATIENTS.

40:03.692 --> 40:06.024
♪ ON A LOVE THAT BURNS
HOT ENOUGH TO LAST ♪
[ SIGHS ] I MISSED IT.

40:06.024 --> 40:07.986
YOU DID.

40:07.986 --> 40:09.077
ARE THEY ALL GONE?

40:09.077 --> 40:11.119
GERHARDT STRAUSS?

40:11.119 --> 40:12.410
WERE THEY PISSED?

40:12.410 --> 40:14.162
NO, ACTUALLY,
IT WENT PRETTY WELL.

40:14.162 --> 40:15.243
THEY ALL SEEMED SOLD.

40:15.243 --> 40:18.587
EXCEPT FOR THE ESTONIAN GUY.
HE WAS LOST.

40:18.587 --> 40:19.878
WAIT. WHAT HAPPENED?

40:19.878 --> 40:21.630
LOOK.
GOOD EVENING.

40:21.630 --> 40:23.131
DR. SHEPHERD WELCOMES YOU ALL

40:23.131 --> 40:27.546
AND REGRETS THAT HE COULDN'T
BE HERE WITH YOU TONIGHT.

40:27.546 --> 40:31.009
♪ OH, I WANNA DANCE
WITH SOMEBODY ♪
HE HAS TAKEN SUDDENLY,
AND VERY DISGUSTINGLY...

40:31.009 --> 40:32.721
[ LAUGHTER ]
...ILL.

40:32.721 --> 40:34.432
I TOLD YOU --
I'VE HEARD IT ENOUGH TIMES.
SO I AM THE WIFE.

40:34.432 --> 40:35.554
YOU DID MY SPEECH.

40:35.554 --> 40:36.975
AND I'M HERE IN HIS STEAD.
WELL...

40:36.975 --> 40:38.226
WHEN MY HUSBAND
WAS FIRST APPROACHED

40:38.226 --> 40:40.519
ABOUT THIS PROJECT,
I WAS NOT ON BOARD.

40:40.519 --> 40:42.320
[ LAUGHTER ]
I KIND OF DID MY SPEECH.

40:42.320 --> 40:43.822
OH, MY GOD.
IT WOULD TAKE
TIME AND ENERGY --

40:43.822 --> 40:45.484
[ CHUCKLES ]
TIME AWAY FROM OUR FAMILY,

40:45.484 --> 40:46.905
OUR MARRIAGE, MY WORK...

40:46.905 --> 40:48.947
HIS WORK.

40:48.947 --> 40:52.831
♪ WITH SOMEBODY WHO LOVES ME ♪
BUT AS I SOON REALIZED,
AS YOU WILL TONIGHT...

40:52.831 --> 40:55.704
[ SIGHS ]
...THAT THIS IS A VITAL
AND MOMENTOUS OPPORTUNITY.

40:55.704 --> 40:58.627
IT IS WORTH EVERY MINUTE
OF YOUR PRECIOUS TIME,

40:58.627 --> 41:00.128
SO LET'S GET STARTED.

41:00.128 --> 41:01.790
[ CHUCKLES ]
EVERYONE KNOWS SOMEONE

41:01.790 --> 41:04.132
WHO HAS SUFFERED
FROM A BRAIN DISORDER.

41:04.132 --> 41:05.544
BUT NONE OF US ARE INVINCIBLE.

41:05.544 --> 41:07.175
[ STOMACH GURGLES ]

41:07.175 --> 41:09.387
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

41:10.889 --> 41:14.472
♪ OH, I WANNA DANCE
WITH SOMEBODY ♪
[ STOMACH GURGLES ]

41:14.472 --> 41:16.054
[ GRUNTS ]

41:16.054 --> 41:17.976
OH, THIS IS BAD.

41:17.976 --> 41:20.899
♪ I WANNA FEEL THE HEAT
WITH SOMEBODY ♪
I'M GOING HOME.

41:20.899 --> 41:24.062
OH, GOD. [ GRUNTS ]

41:24.062 --> 41:26.234
AND WE'LL HAVE DR. YANG
COME AND EXPLAIN IT.

41:26.234 --> 41:28.066
♪ YEAH, I WANNA DANCE
WITH SOMEBODY ♪
FRANCESCA'S PACEMAKER
IS FUNCTIONING WELL,

41:28.066 --> 41:30.108
AND I REVIEWED
IVY'S POST-OP ECHO

41:30.108 --> 41:33.071
AND SAW NO SIGNS
OF GRAFT FAILURE.
NOW THE BAD NEWS?

41:33.071 --> 41:35.203
♪ WITH SOMEBODY WHO LOVES ME ♪
UNFORTUNATELY,

41:35.203 --> 41:37.205
THE BIOPSY DID NOT SHOW
A VIRAL CAUSE.

41:37.205 --> 41:38.787
SO WHAT'S CAUSING THIS?

41:38.787 --> 41:40.078
Owen:
WE'D LIKE TO RUN MORE TESTS.

41:40.078 --> 41:42.080
MAYBE EVEN HAVE SOMEONE

41:42.080 --> 41:43.712
EVALUATE YOUR HOME
FOR OTHER EXPOSURES.

41:43.712 --> 41:45.083
WE HAVE NO IDEA.

41:45.083 --> 41:47.295
WE DON'T KNOW WHAT'S CAUSING
THEIR HEARTS TO FAIL.

41:47.295 --> 41:49.588
♪ OH, I WANNA DANCE
WITH SOMEBODY ♪
BUT THE GOOD NEWS IS
WE CAUGHT IT,

41:49.588 --> 41:50.799
AND WE'RE TREATING IT.

41:50.799 --> 41:53.892
[ COUGHING ]

41:53.892 --> 41:57.976
♪ I WANNA FEEL THE HEAT
WITH SOMEBODY ♪

41:57.976 --> 41:59.898
EVENTUALLY, WE HAVE TO FACE

41:59.898 --> 42:01.059
THE FACT THAT WE'RE HUMAN...

42:01.059 --> 42:02.941
♪ YEAH, I WANNA DANCE
WITH SOMEBODY ♪

42:02.941 --> 42:06.444
I'M NOT SICK.
I'M OKAY.

42:06.444 --> 42:08.406
[ COUGHING RESUMES ]
...AND THAT SOMETIMES...

42:08.406 --> 42:13.652
♪ WITH SOMEBODY WHO LOVES ME ♪
...EVEN THE MIGHTIEST OF US
NEED HELP.

42:13.652 --> 42:15.113
[ SIREN WAILS ]
